msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:106
msgid "Combat Sensors"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:107
msgid "BBs get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:109
msgid "When a BB is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:114
msgid "Afterburners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:115
msgid ""
"After researching Fighters, all of your Fighters get +1 on their Attack "
"when firing on ships with a Hull Size of 1 (or less, if playing with the "
"Insectoids)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:117 app/data/card_manifest.py:125
msgid "When a Fighter is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:122
msgid "Photon Bomb"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:123
msgid ""
"After researching Fighters, all of your Fighters get +1 on their Attack "
"when firing on ships with a Hull Size greater than 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:130
msgid "Stim Packs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:131
msgid "All Ground Units get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:133
msgid "In ground combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:138
msgid "Improved Crew's Quarters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:139
msgid "CAs cost 3 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:146
msgid "Phased Warp Coil"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:147
msgid "BCs cost 3 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:154
msgid "Advanced Ordnance Storage System"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:155
msgid "BBs cost 4 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:162
msgid "The Captain's Chair"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:163
msgid "DNs cost 4 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:170
msgid "Efficient Factories"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:171
msgid ""
"Non-Barren, Non-Homeworld Colonies that will produce 5 CP this Economic "
"Phase produce 6 CP instead. The max gain is 8 CP on normal maps. In "
"situations where one of these fully grown colonies would produce "
"something other than 5 CP, the colony produces 1 extra CP when fully "
"grown."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:173
msgid "Non-Barren, Non-Homeworld"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:174
msgid ""
"The max gain is 8 CP on normal maps. In situations where one of these "
"fully grown colonies would produce something other than 5 CP, the colony "
"produces 1 extra CP when fully grown."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:181
msgid "Omega Crystals"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:182
msgid ""
"All the player's CAs, BCs, BBs, DNs, and Titans are equipped with the "
"Omega Crystal. If a ship with the Omega Crystal is present in battle the "
"player may activate it after a Group has fired (enemy or friendly). That "
"Group must reroll ALL of its dice. The first set of results from that "
"Group is undone and replaced by the new rolls. The new results must be "
"accepted, even if worse for the Omega Crystal player. No matter how many "
"ships with the Omega Crystal are present, the player may only ever do "
"this once during the entire battle. If the ships retreat and then "
"subsequently engage in battle, they may again use the Omega Crystal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:184 app/data/card_manifest.py:208
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:224 app/data/card_manifest.py:232
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1623 app/data/card_manifest.py:1681
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2110
msgid "When first used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:189
msgid "Cryogenic Stasis Pods"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:190
msgid "Boarding Ships & Transports pay 1/2 maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:197
msgid "Minesweep Jammer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:198
msgid ""
"Minesweepers used against you are treated as having one level less of "
"Minesweeping technology. So Minesweepers with only level 1 would not "
"sweep any Mines at all."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:200
msgid "At the start of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:205
msgid "Air Support"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:206
msgid ""
"Transports function in ground combat as B6-2-x2 units. (They must survive"
" the space combat to be used this way.) Only the modifiers for Ground "
"Units are applied to Transports being used as Air Support. Any damage "
"that they took during the space battle is considered repaired before the "
"start of the ground combat. They may be fired at by opposing Ground "
"Units. They may not be removed to garrison the planet. If no other Ground"
" Units are available to be removed to garrison the planet, the planet is "
"not captured."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:213
msgid "Hidden Turret"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:214
msgid "Minesweepers fire as E3 units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:216
msgid "When a SW is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:221
msgid "Stealth Field Emitter"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:222
msgid "Your ships go back to their unrevealed side after combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:229
msgid "Advanced Comm Array"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:230
msgid ""
"If a ship otherwise qualifies for the Reaction Move ability, they may "
"react into an adjacent, non-battle hex when an opponent moves into that "
"hex. This stops the other player's movement. During combat, the reacting "
"player is considered the attacker in that battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:237
msgid "Mobile Analysis Bay"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:238
msgid ""
"You can gain technology from captured ships in any Economic Phase after "
"they are captured without having to scrap them. They do not have to be at"
" a Shipyard. May only be used one time on each captured ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:245
msgid "Adaptive Cloaking Device"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:246
msgid ""
"If your enemy does not have Scanners equal to or greater than your "
"Cloaking, your Raiders fire with a +2 to their Attack Strength (instead "
"of the usual +1) in the 1st Round. If they do have Scanners equal to your"
" Cloaking then your Cloak is nullified, but in the 1st Round they fire as"
" A-Class, 2nd Round as B-Class, 3rd Round as C-Class, 4th & later as "
"D-Class. This card only impacts Raiders, even if you also have the "
"Cloaking Geniuses Empire Advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:248
msgid "When a Raider is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:253
msgid "Fearless Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:254
msgid ""
"The ethos of this race places a high value on proving their courage. All "
"of their combat-capable ships and Shipyards (excluding Boarding Ships and"
" Ground Units) fire as A-Class ships in the first round of combat (only)."
" Their Missiles hit as C-Class in the first round. After the first round "
"everything reverts to its normal Class. However, none of their ships are "
"able to retreat from combat until after Round 3 (this may be modified by "
"e.g. Crew Cards). Their ships would still fire as E-Class (or F-Class for"
" Boarding Ships) when in Asteroids or Nebulae (5.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:256
msgid "Their Missiles hit as C-Class in the first round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:258 app/data/card_manifest.py:266
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:289 app/data/card_manifest.py:323
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:368
msgid "When first entering any combat, including Aliens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:263
msgid "Warrior Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:264
msgid ""
"+1 to Attack Strength for all non-Boarding Ship units when they are the "
"attacker in a battle. –1 to the Attack Strength for all non-Boarding Ship"
" units when they are the defender in a battle. No advantage is given when"
" bombarding a planet or to ground troops."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:271
msgid "Celestial Knights"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:272
msgid ""
"Once per space battle (not ground combat or Colony bombardment), after "
"the first round, at the start of a round, this race may declare a "
"\"charge\". All of their units (including Boarding Ships and Missile "
"Boats but not any kind of Bases, DSN, Ion Cannons and Shipyards) get two "
"attacks (or fire two missiles) in that round only. However, in all "
"following rounds all enemy units get +1 to their Attack Strength (this "
"does not apply to fire against Missiles, but does apply against any kind "
"of Bases, DSN, and Shipyards). In addition, the charging ships may not "
"retreat the round after the charge."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:274
msgid "and Missile Boats"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:275
msgid "DSN, Ion Cannons"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:276
msgid "(or fire two missiles)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:277
msgid ""
"(this does not apply to fire against Missiles, but does apply against any"
" kind of Bases, DSN, and Shipyards)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:279
msgid "When a \"charge\" is declared for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:284
msgid "Giant Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:285
msgid ""
"The Hull Size of all units (except Ground Units and Missiles) of this "
"race is increased by one. This impacts everything that has to do with "
"Hull Size – SYs needed to construct (including for Miners, Colony Ships, "
"and MS Pipelines), damage to destroy, technology that can be carried, "
"maintenance, boarding parties, etc. The cost to build the ships remains "
"the same. Captured ships of this race retain their Hull Size. Giant Race "
"may not research Fighters and may not get them by any other means "
"(capturing technology, etc.). Decoys continue to have a Hull Size of zero"
" and do not need a SY to build. Missiles still only take 1 hit to "
"destroy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:287
msgid "Missiles still only take 1 hit to destroy"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:294
msgid "Industrious Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:295
msgid ""
"When this race researches Terraforming 1, they may colonize Asteroids "
"exactly as if they were a Barren Planet. The Asteroids still retain their"
" normal terrain effects. Titans may not destroy an Asteroid like it would"
" a planet and may not attack Asteroid Colonies at all. Other players may "
"not attack an Asteroid Colony with Ground Units. If playing with the "
"Short Game Victory Condition (Colony Points; CSB 1.1.7), Asteroid "
"Colonies in Deep Space do not count as a Colony Point. If colonizing an "
"Asteroid, the player does NOT get an Alien Technology Card (11.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:297
msgid "When an asteroid is colonized for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:302
msgid "Ancient Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:303
msgid ""
"At the start of the game (before it begins), this player reveals that "
"they are the Ancient Race, then explores all hexes adjacent to their "
"Homeworld. They then explore six of the hexes that are adjacent to those "
"hexes (these will be two hexes from their Homeworld). This means that it "
"is possible for some of the hexes that are two spaces away from their "
"Homeworld to not be explored (depending on the setup). They immediately "
"collect up to 3 Minerals that were revealed and place those Minerals on "
"their Homeworld. Next, this player places up to 3 Colony Ships from their"
" supply (Colony Ship side up) on any non-barren planets that are revealed"
" in this way (3 Colony Ships still start at the Homeworld). They will "
"become Colony 1s at the end of the first Economic Phase. This represents "
"colonists that have made contact with this player's race again after "
"spending hundreds of years in cryogenic sleep while in transit to these "
"planets. Now that the \"modern\" faster than light drive has been "
"perfected, the Colonies will grow and become part of the Empire."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:305
msgid "At the start of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:310
msgid "Space Pilgrims"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:311
msgid ""
"This race has a greater understanding of space and is at home in it. They"
" suffer no movement penalties in Nebulae or Asteroids. Their ships never "
"get sucked into Black Holes and they are never Lost in Space. They may "
"even use the Black Hole Slingshot optional rule automatically, without "
"having to roll for destruction. They still are destroyed by Danger! "
"markers and other terrain still affects them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:313
msgid ""
"When entering a Black Hole or Lost in Space marker or if they ignore the "
"movement penalty of an Asteroid or Nebula. In order to keep their "
"advantage secret, they may choose to roll when entering a Black Hole hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:318
msgid "Hive Mind"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:319
msgid ""
"This race learns and adapts in each battle. Starting in round 2 of a "
"battle, all of this race's units get +1 to their Defense Strength. "
"Starting in round 4, all units also get +1 to their Attack Strength. "
"Starting in round 6, all units get +1 to their Hull Size. These same "
"modifiers also apply to ground combat, but the ground combat is "
"considered to have started with round 1 even if a space battle preceded "
"it. If the attacker does not get to fire in the first round of ground "
"combat (because of not having Drop Ships), that still counts as the first"
" round of combat. They do not get these benefits while bombarding "
"planets. Missiles receive the attack and defense strength benefits, but "
"not the hull size benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:321
msgid ""
"Missiles receive the attack and defense strength benefits, but not the "
"hull size benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:328
msgid "Nano-technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:329
msgid ""
"This race's units may instantly upgrade to the newest technology for free"
" regardless of location. If they do so they must not move that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:336
msgid "Quick Learners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:337
msgid ""
"These start with Military Academy level 1 and roll 2 dice (taking the "
"best result) when checking to see if a ship increases in Experience. "
"Other Empires may NEVER gain Military Academy technology from this race."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:339
msgid "When rolling to see if a ship gains Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:344
msgid "Gifted Scientists"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:345
#, python-format
msgid ""
"This highly technological race gets a 33% discount (rounded up and "
"applied before any other discounts) when researching any technology. "
"However, every unit they build (Colony Ship, Decoy, Scout, Pipeline, "
"etc.) costs 1 CP more."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:352
msgid "Master Engineers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:353
msgid ""
"This race uses a highly advanced, but unstable form of faster-than-light "
"drive. This empire starts the game with Move 2 and Fast 1 technologies. "
"In addition, each full-strength colony can produce and retrofit ships as "
"if it had 1 SY present. This may be combined with actual SY that are "
"built.\n"
"EXAMPLE: A Full Strength Colony without an SY and with SY Tech 3 could "
"produce a BC."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:356
msgid "This empire starts the game with Move 2 and Fast 1 technologies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:363
msgid "Insectoids"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:364
msgid ""
"This race reproduces and builds very rapidly. The Hull Size of all units "
"(except Ground Units and Missiles) of this race is decreased by one. "
"Except as noted, this impacts everything that has to do with Hull Size – "
"SYs needed to construct (including for Miners, Colony Ships, and MS "
"pipelines), damage to destroy, tech that can be carried, maintenance, "
"boarding parties, etc. The cost to build the ships remains the same. A "
"ship such as a DD, which has a Hull Size of 0, would pay no maintenance, "
"not be allowed to carry any attack or defense tech, and could upgrade "
"technology at a SY for no CP cost. A ship with a Hull Size of 0 would "
"still be destroyed by 1 hit and would be considered to have a Hull Size "
"of 1 for the purpose of any Experience roll. Ships with a Hull Size of 0 "
"are considered to have a Hull Size of 1/2 for the purpose of using "
"Shipyard capacity. For example: 1 Shipyard at Shipyard Tech 2 could build"
" 3 DDs in an Economic Phase. Insectoids may not research Military "
"Academies or Fighters and may not get them by any means (capturing "
"technology, etc.). Captured ships of this race retain their Hull Size. "
"Insectoid Starbases may still mount Attack 4."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:366
msgid "Insectoid Starbases may still mount Attack 4."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:373
msgid "Immortals"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:374
msgid ""
"This race reproduces very slowly, but never dies of old age. They have "
"developed extra shielding and a system of reserve power in an attempt to "
"preserve the lives of their people. One time in each round of combat, "
"this race may choose to ignore one point of damage. This means that it is"
" impossible for one of their ships to be destroyed in a one-on-one battle"
" (unless the other ship is a Titan or Missile Boat or uses Resource "
"Cards). An Alternate Empire player cannot ignore a hit against one of "
"their Missiles. However, because a large seed population is needed for "
"their Colonies, each Colony Ship costs 2 CP more. They may not choose to "
"ignore a boarding hit. Captured ships retain this ability. However, only "
"a hit on the captured ship(s) can be ignored. Immortals may not research "
"Boarding and may not get it by any means (capturing technology, etc.). If"
" playing with any rule that normally would allow a player to carry CP "
"over into the start of the game (like the Technology Head Start Scenario "
"Modifier), the Immortals may not and will lose any CP not spent on "
"research. Immortals cannot use their special ability against Bombardment "
"Damage or during Ground Combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:376
msgid "unless the other ship is a Titan or Missile Boat or uses Resource Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:377
msgid "like the Technology Head Start Scenario Modifier"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:379
msgid "When they first choose to ignore 1 hit in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:384
msgid "Expert Tacticians"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:385
msgid ""
"This race of superior tacticians gets the +1 Attack Fleet Size Bonus as "
"soon as they have one more combat-capable ship in a battle than their "
"opponent (they don't need to have a 2:1 advantage). In addition, "
"opponents do not get the Fleet Size Bonus against them unless they "
"outnumber them by 3:1. If the opposing fleet has Agent Smith or has an "
"Admiral Of The Navy (or any combination thereof), everything cancels each"
" other out and the Fleet Size Bonus is given at 2:1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:387
msgid "When they first choose to use their improved Fleet Size Bonuses in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:392
msgid "Horsemen of the Plains"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:393
msgid ""
"This race developed from a culture that valued the ability to strike "
"quickly and evade. If a ship of this race could otherwise retreat, it may"
" do so at the end of a round of combat, even if it fired during that "
"round. It does not need to wait for its turn to fire to retreat. They "
"could retreat as early as the end of Round 1, before Round 2 begins. In "
"addition, all of this player's ships always get +2 to their Attack "
"Strength when firing on a planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:395
msgid "When they first use one of their abilities."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:400
msgid "And We Still Carry Swords"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:401
msgid ""
"This race loves physical combat. This race starts with Ground Combat 2. "
"All of their boarding attacks get +1 to their Attack Strength and all "
"boarding attacks against them get -1 to their Attack Strength. In "
"addition, all of their Ground Units, including Militia, get +1 to their "
"Attack and Defense Strength (whether attacking or defending). Other "
"Empires may NEVER gain Ground Combat tech from this race."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:403
msgid "When engaging in boarding attack or ground invasion for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:408 app/data/card_manifest.py:847
#: app/data/master_rulebook.py:2179
msgid "Amazing Diplomats"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:409
msgid ""
"Non-Player Aliens do not attack this race and this race may both move "
"through their System and stack with them. NPAs with the Aggressive trait "
"do not attack them. While the alien ships will not leave the System, they"
" will defend against attacks from other players. This player may colonize"
" alien planets as if the aliens were not there (and gain an Alien "
"Technology card). This represents them developing a relationship, trade, "
"and an outpost on that planet. A Colony on an alien planet is treated "
"like a player's Colony in every respect. If the alien ships are "
"subsequently destroyed by another player, the Colony still continues "
"until destroyed normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:411
msgid ""
"When entering a NPA hex for the first time or if Aggressive NPA would "
"attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:416
msgid "Traders"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:417
msgid "Gets one extra CP for each colony connected by an MS Pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:424
msgid "Cloaking Geniuses"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:425
msgid ""
"After researching Cloaking 1, all of their Scouts and Destroyers also get"
" the benefit of Cloaking. After researching Cloaking level 2, all of "
"their Cruisers also get the benefit of Cloaking. If not nullified by "
"scanners the SCs, DDs & CAs do get the +1 to their Attack Strength during"
" the first firing round. If nullified by Scanners, these ships fire where"
" they normally would according to their Weapon Class rating (a CA would "
"fire as C-Class). This is not an instant upgrade. Any ships already "
"produced would have to be refitted. A note will need to be made on "
"existing Groups in the margin of the Ship Technology Sheet. Captured "
"ships of this race retain their Cloaking ability (and can be upgraded)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:427
msgid ""
"When a cloaked SC/DD/CA is encountered in combat or moves through an "
"enemy ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:432
msgid "Star Wolves"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:433
msgid ""
"Each of this race's SCs, DDs, and Fighters get +1 to their Attack "
"Strength when firing on a unit with a Hull Size of 2 or greater. In "
"addition, their DDs cost 1 less (8 CP for Base Empires, or 9 CP for "
"Alternate Empires)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:435
msgid "(8 CP for Base Empires, or 9 CP for Alternate Empires)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:437
msgid "When they first use their ability."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:442
msgid "Power to the People"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:443
msgid ""
"Mines, Colony Ships, Miners, and MS Pipelines are automatically and "
"instantly upgraded to the player's current Movement technology (they will"
" be able to move more than 1 space per turn)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:445
msgid ""
"When a Miner, CO, MS Pipeline, or revealed Mine moves faster than normal "
"for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:450
msgid "House of Speed"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:451
msgid ""
"This race starts with Movement 7 tech, but their ships sacrifice "
"defensive abilities. Opponents (including NPAs, Doomsday Machines, Space "
"Amoebas, and Space Pirates) get a +2 to their Attack Strength (even when "
"boarding) when firing at ships of this race (including Fighters, but not "
"any type of Bases, SYs, DSN, Colonies, Space Stations, or Ground Units)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:453
msgid ""
"The first time a ship moves more than 1 hex in a turn or the first time "
"its ships are in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:458
msgid "Powerful Psychics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:459
msgid ""
"This race starts with Exploration 1 technology. In addition, their "
"sensors are more advanced. This player may reveal all face down Groups "
"that are adjacent to one of their ships with Exploration technology (e.g."
" CAs, Flagship, Unique ships). These counters are left face up (as if "
"they had been encountered in combat). However, the technology on the "
"revealed ships is not revealed by this power. Since their Exploration "
"technology is partially based on their psychic powers, other Empires may "
"NEVER gain Exploration technology from this race (either by scrapping "
"boarded ships or capturing planets)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:461
msgid "The first time a stack is inspected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:466
msgid "Shape Shifters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:467
msgid ""
"This Empire may place Decoys in any hex with a friendly combat ship in "
"addition to any hex with a Colony. Each Economic Phase they get two free "
"Decoy units. If they run out of Decoys, they may use any spare counter as"
" a Decoy if they mark it as such on their Ship Tech sheet.\n"
"EXAMPLE: CA #2 can be marked as a Decoy on the Ship Tech Sheet and used "
"as a Decoy.\n"
"In combat, they do not have to reveal any technology possessed unless it "
"actually would change the result of a combat roll, in which case they "
"announce it after the roll.\n"
"EXAMPLE: A CA Group has Attack 2 Tech. This is not revealed. After "
"rolling an Attack, one of the dice misses by one. The player then must "
"reveal that he has Attack 2 and it scores a hit.\n"
"Once per game, they may retreat their ships as if they had just played "
"Resource Card #107 Retreat While Engaged."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:473
msgid "played Resource Card #107 Retreat While Engaged."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:475
msgid "When a non-Decoy effect of this card is used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:480
msgid "On Board Workshop"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:481
msgid ""
"Each CV, BV, and Titan may be used to build one Fighter during the "
"Economic Phase as long as there is room to store the Fighter built. This "
"includes Fighter technology that has just been researched. The Fighter "
"costs the same as if it was produced at a Shipyard. No other ships that "
"carry Fighters (like Unique ships) can do this except Alternate Empire "
"BBs and DNs. During a Movement Turn, one Fighter may be refitted and the "
"ship carrying it may move as long as the FTR accompanies it for the "
"entire movement phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:483
msgid "Alternate Empire BBs and DNs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:485
msgid "When a CV/BV/Titan is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:490
msgid "Superhighway"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:491
msgid ""
"Each ship that spends its entire move on an MS Pipeline chain may move "
"two extra hexes instead of one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:492
msgid ""
"The flavor text on the card comes from an old German slogan against speed"
" limits on the autobahn—roughly, \"Free roads for free citizens\"."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:494
msgid "The first time it is used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:499
msgid "On the Move"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:500
msgid ""
"Shipyards and all types of Bases have Move 1 and may attack and explore. "
"They may not retreat from combat, and they can never be upgraded to a "
"higher Movement technology. They may move an extra hex if using MS "
"Pipelines or Black Hole Slingshot. Shipyards may only build ships during "
"the Economic Phase if they are in the same hex with a friendly Colony "
"that produced CP during this Economic Phase. However, they may be used to"
" upgrade ships normally no matter where they are on the map. Both the SY "
"and group being upgraded may not move when performing the retrofit. All "
"other rules for Shipyards and Bases are the same."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:502
msgid ""
"The first time a revealed Shipyard/Base moves, the first time a Shipyard "
"or a (non advanced) Base is revealed while not at a Colony, or the first "
"time a Shipyard/Base is in battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:507
msgid "Longbowmen"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:508
msgid ""
"This race uses long range torpedoes. The Weapon Class of their SC, DD, "
"CA, BC, Flagship, Missiles, and nullified Raiders is increased by one "
"letter (C-Class becomes B-Class, B-Class becomes A-Class, etc.). A-Class "
"ships remain A-Class and get no benefit. This benefit is only if the "
"battle is in open space, Space Stations, planets, Minerals, or Space "
"Wrecks. DDs with Long Lance Torpedoes and Fighters stay at B-Class and "
"get no benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:510
msgid "SC, DD, CA, BC, Flagship, Missiles, and nullified Raiders"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:512
msgid ""
"When first entering combat, including Aliens, with one of the affected "
"ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:517
msgid "Fast Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:518
msgid ""
"Replicators start with Move 2 tech. Future levels of Movement technology "
"only cost 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:525
msgid "Green Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:526
msgid "Replicator Colonies do not begin to deplete until Econ Phase 13."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:528
msgid "At the start of Economic Phase 10."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:533
msgid "Improved Gunnery"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:534
msgid ""
"The Replicator Flagship and all Type XIII and Type XV ships are equipped "
"with Second Salvo. When they start a turn with 4 RP, all of their ships "
"have their Tactics level increased by 1 and type V ships gain +1 Attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:536 app/data/card_manifest.py:2093
msgid "Second Salvo"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:538
msgid ""
"When entering combat, including Aliens, with a Type V, XIII, XV or the "
"Flagship, or when a ship reveals a higher Tactics level for any reason."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:543 app/data/card_manifest.py:546
msgid "Warp Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:544
msgid ""
"Replicator Explore Ships and the Flagship are equipped with Warp Gates. "
"Explore ships still have a Hull Size of 2, but only take one hull to "
"produce (and only count as one hull if converted to a different ship)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:548
msgid ""
"The first time a Warp Gate is used, or a ship equipped with one is in "
"combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:553
msgid "Advanced Research"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:554
msgid "Replicators begin the game with one extra RP. Buying RP costs only 25."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:561
msgid "Replicator Capitol"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:562
msgid ""
"The Replicator Homeworld may produce an additional Hull every odd "
"Economic Phase (in addition to any other increases e.g. from spending "
"CP). The Replicators also start with 10 extra CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:569
msgid "Red Squadron"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:573
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. One FTR "
"Group currently in battle gets an additional +1 to attack for the "
"remainder of the battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:580
msgid "Sensor Blind Spot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:584
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. A single "
"unit with a cloak that has been nullified by Scanners during combat may "
"hide in the sensor blind spot of a unit with Hull Size x3 or greater. The"
" Raider immediately makes a retreat from battle. This doesn't need to be "
"a hex closer to a friendly Colony than the hex the battle was in."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:591
msgid "Self Destruct"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:595
msgid ""
"Play after one of your ships is captured. Immediately destroy it. The "
"enemy gains no knowledge of your abilities from capturing this ship. The "
"ship still counts as captured for the purpose of Ship Experience "
"Promotion Rolls (37.3.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:602
msgid "Concealed Minefield"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:606
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. Before Enemy"
" Minesweepers sweep your Mines, one of your Mines may detonate as normal "
"– even against a Minesweeper (17.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:613 app/data/card_manifest.py:626
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:639 app/data/card_manifest.py:652
msgid "Heroic Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:617 app/data/card_manifest.py:630
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:643 app/data/card_manifest.py:656
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. Select one "
"of the ships listed on the card title (a single ship, not a Group). It is"
" Heroic for the rest of the game. Heroic ships get +1 to their Attack and"
" Defense. They also take one more hit to destroy (this is cumulative with"
" the Legendary bonus; 37.0). They do not pay maintenance. Heroic status "
"is lost if the ship is captured or destroyed. Instead of using a number "
"counter under the ship, use one of the Heroic counters with a star on it."
" If the ship ever gets flipped face down again, it will look like any "
"other ship. In the very rare case where a player may have 2 Heroic ships "
"of the same type in the same hex, they may flip the Heroic counter to the"
" 2-star side.\n"
"When playing with Crew Cards (12.0), these Resource Cards cannot be used "
"to make ships Heroic. Instead, they can be played at any time to draw 2 "
"Crew Cards and keep 1. They may be immediately assigned or assigned "
"during the next Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:619
msgid ""
"\"There will always be a Rodger Young in the Federation fleet.\" Inspired"
" by Admiral Ernest J. King who stated that \"There’ll always be an "
"England in the United States Navy.\" This was in response to DE-635 USS "
"England’s sinking six Japanese Submarines between 18-27 May 1944."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:620 app/data/card_manifest.py:633
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:646 app/data/card_manifest.py:658
msgid ""
"Play this card to build an extra Hull on the Replicator Homeworld. Only "
"one of these cards may be played at the start of an  economic Phase. This"
" card may be combined with buying an extra Hull and with the Replicator "
"Capitol Empire Advantage so that up to 4 Hulls could theoretically be "
"produced in one Economic Phase. Since it only takes three ships of Hull "
"Size 1 to build a Type XIII or Type XV, in this extreme case the "
"Replicator could theoretically build a Type XIII or XV AND another Hull "
"Size 1 ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:632
msgid ""
"\"All Hands to General Quarters! ECM to Maximum! Hard a Port! Prepare to "
"engage a major portion of the enemy fleet.\" Inspired by the orders given"
" by Commander Evans aboard DD-557 USS Johnston at the Battle of Leyte "
"Gulf."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:645
msgid ""
"\"The Empire expects every member of this crew to do his duty today!\" "
"Inspired by Admiral Nelson’s speech before the Battle of Trafalgar."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:664 app/data/card_manifest.py:676
msgid "Heroic Ground Unit"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:668 app/data/card_manifest.py:680
msgid ""
"Play before the first round of a ground battle begins. Select one of your"
" non-Militia Ground Units (one unit, not an entire Group). It will be "
"Heroic for the rest of the game or until it is destroyed. Heroic Ground "
"Units get +1 to their Attack/Defense/Hull Size. This card may not be "
"combined with Defending Familiar Terrain to create a Heroic Heavy "
"Infantry Militia."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:669
msgid ""
"\"For the Honor of the Regiment!\" The art used for this card is the "
"crest of the regiment that Oliver Upshaw, this game’s developer, served "
"in."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:670
msgid "Extra Hull. See the note for Card #70."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:681
msgid ""
"Play this card to build an extra Hull on the Replicator Homeworld. Only "
"one of these cards may be played at the start of an economic Phase. This "
"card may be combined with buying an extra Hull and with the Replicator "
"Capitol Empire Advantage so that up to 4 Hulls could theoretically be "
"produced in one Economic Phase. Since it only takes three ships of Hull "
"Size 1 to build a Type XIII or Type XV, in this extreme case the "
"Replicator could theoretically build a Type XIII or XV AND another Hull "
"Size 1 ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:687 app/data/card_manifest.py:1525
msgid "Defending Familiar Terrain"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:691 app/data/card_manifest.py:1529
msgid ""
"Play before the first round of a ground battle to upgrade a planet's "
"Militia to Heavy Infantry for the duration of the combat (21.10). May "
"even be played if the defender is only at Ground Combat 1. May be played "
"when another player attacks NPAs. A counter is provided so that the "
"players can keep separate any real defending Infantry/Heavy Infantry."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:692 app/data/card_manifest.py:703
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:714 app/data/card_manifest.py:725
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:736 app/data/card_manifest.py:749
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1530
msgid ""
"Extra Move. Play this card before moving to move one Replicator ship (not"
" a Group), one extra space this turn. Additionally, for each other "
"Resource Card you discard unused from your hand, one additional "
"Replicator ship that is part of the same Group can also move one extra "
"space. Two of these cards cannot be used in combination to make one "
"Replicator ship move two extra spaces in one move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:698
msgid "Research Breakthrough"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:702
msgid ""
"Play this card to allow you to research two levels of the same technology"
" in the same Economic Phase at the combined cost of the technologies in "
"question plus 5 CP. If you are using IC/RC rules (36.0), the extra cost "
"is 5 RP. This is the only card effect that cannot be canceled when "
"played. When you discard it, you do not have to announce if it was played"
" for its effect or for CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:709
msgid "Quick Study"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:713
msgid ""
"Play before a friendly or enemy Group rolls for Experience. Shift the "
"dice result by +/–2. This affects all Experience die rolls made by that "
"Group this round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:720
msgid "Discover Member of Ancient Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:724
msgid ""
"Play at the start of an Econ Phase where you will roll on the Space Wreck"
" Technology Table. After you roll, you may add or subtract up to 2 to the"
" dice, even looping through the results. For example, a 10 can be shifted"
" to a 2 and a 2 can be shifted to a 10."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:731
msgid "Overload Weapons"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:735
msgid ""
"For this effect, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. Play before one of your ships (not Group) fires. When "
"calculating the number needed to get a hit, double the Attack tech that "
"is on the ship. For example, a BC with Attack 1 would have an Attack "
"Strength of 7. If a hit is scored the target takes an extra 2 points of "
"damage. This means a SC could one shot kill a DN/BB/Base with this card. "
"If used on a Missile Boat, the card must be played when placing the "
"Missile, doubles the Missiles attack tech, and the Missile would do 4 "
"damage if it hits. For the rest of the battle the selected ship's Attack "
"Strength is considered to be zero. The Ship Selected must mount at least "
"Attack 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:738
msgid ""
"If used on a Missile Boat, the card must be played when placing the "
"Missile, doubles the Missiles attack tech, and the Missile would do 4 "
"damage if it hits."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:744
msgid "Unconventional Boarding"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:748
msgid ""
"For this effect, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. Play this card instead of performing your ship's normal "
"attacks. Select an enemy ship and attack it with a boarding strength of "
"5. Subtract the Hull Size of the targeted ship from this Attack Strength."
" Security Forces have no effect on this die roll. And We Still Carry "
"Swords (Empire Advantage #47) gives the +1/–1 bonus as normal. "
"Experience, except for the extra Hull of a Legendary/Heroic Ship, has no "
"effect on this roll. Add 2 to this Attack Strength if you have researched"
" Boarding 1. Add 2 more if you have researched Boarding 2. This can only "
"be used against ships that normally can be boarded. If you are not "
"playing with Boarding Ships (19.0), then this card cannot be played for "
"its effect. This effect can't be used against Replicators and cannot be "
"used by or against Alternate Empires or Immortals."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:751
msgid ""
"This effect can't be used against Replicators and cannot be used by or "
"against Alternate Empires or Immortals."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:757
msgid "Xeno-Archeology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:761
msgid ""
"If you spend 10 CP in the next Econ Phase, you may keep the second Alien "
"Tech card that you drew when capturing a planet (11.1). This card must be"
" played before discarding one of the Alien Tech cards. If played, the 10 "
"CP must be spent in the next Econ Phase. If playing without non-player "
"Aliens, the player must normally spend 10 CP to keep one Alien Technology"
" Card. Xeno-Archeology could be played to allow the player to spend an "
"additional 10 CP to keep the other card. If this card is canceled the 10 "
"CP does not have to be paid."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:762
msgid ""
"After having earned an Alien Technology Card, gain an RP instead of 10 "
"CP. Replicator player plays this immediately upon earning an Alien Tech "
"Card. If this card is canceled, the Replicator player still gets to turn "
"in the Alien Tech Card for 10 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:768
msgid "Missed Rendezvous"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:772
msgid ""
"Play before ships are revealed in battle. If the other side has units "
"participating in this battle that entered the hex from at least two "
"different hex sides or via Reaction Movement (35.0), all ships entering "
"through a selected hexside do not show up until the second round of "
"combat. These ships cannot retreat until the third round. For the delayed"
" units, the second round is treated as the first round, the third round "
"as the second, etc. in all respects (including when using the Empire "
"Advantages #31 Fearless Race, #38 Hive Mind, etc.) Minesweepers that "
"arrive on the second round of combat cannot sweep any remaining Mines. "
"Ships with Shield Projectors that arrive on the second round of combat "
"can only protect ships that also arrived in the second round of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:779
msgid "Activate Space Monstrosity"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:783
msgid ""
"Play before Doomsday Machines (29.0) move or Space Amoebas spread (SSB "
"3.0 and CSB 10.0). Choose a Doomsday Machine or Space Amoeba. You "
"determine where it moves/spreads to, not the normal rules of the game. "
"Though you cannot select a Black Hole hex for a Space Amoeba to spread to"
" and you cannot move the DM/SA into a player's Home System hexes. The DM "
"can still only move up to two hexes and the SA will still only spread to "
"one hex. If not playing with either Doomsday Machines or Space Amoebas, "
"this card can't be used for its event."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:790
msgid "Spawn Doomsday Machine"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:794
msgid ""
"For this effect, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. This card must be played at the start of your turn prior "
"to your movement. Place a Doomsday Machine (29.0) in a Deep Space hex "
"that is adjacent to one of your SC/SCXs and does not contain any terrain "
"or unit counters. This does not cause an unrevealed SC/SCX to become "
"revealed. It is not under any player's control and will operate according"
" to the rules in section 29.0. If not playing with DMs, the card cannot "
"be played for its effect. If this card is played successfully for its "
"effect, it does not go into your discard pile; it is set aside and is "
"unusable for the rest of the game. For this card Replicator Type 0, II, "
"and IV ships are considered a SC/SCX."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:801
msgid "Spy on Board"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:805
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Econ Phase to flip over"
" all the enemy units or NPA Aliens in one hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:812
msgid "Provide Cover"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:816
msgid ""
"Play after an enemy Group targets one of your Groups. Designate another "
"one of your Groups as the target of the attack. The target you choose may"
" not be a Titan, any Base, Defense Satellite Network, Ion Cannon, "
"Shipyard, or CV/BV (if you have Fighters present), or be protected by "
"Shield Projector. It must be a legal target. All ships in the enemy Group"
" must fire at the designated Group for this round of battle. They gain +1"
" to their attack. If your Group is destroyed before the last enemy ship "
"in the Group has fired the remaining ships can pick new targets and do "
"not get the +1. If the Group selected has not fired yet and it survives "
"it must fire at the enemy Group that it blocked for this round. It will "
"also gain a +1. It it destroys the enemy Group, it can switch remaining "
"shots to new targets but doesn't get the +1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:819
msgid "Defense Satellite Network, Ion Cannon"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:825
msgid "Alien Reinforcements"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:829
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn, the start of an Economic Phase or the "
"start of combat before ships are revealed. Select one un-colonized Deep "
"Space planet that has at least one NPA ship and randomly add 3 NPA ships "
"to it (18.0). If you are not playing with NPAs then this card cannot be "
"played for its effect. If the Replicators are in combat with the NPAs, "
"these added ships may make it possible for them to mark off having "
"encountered a Fleet Size of 5 or greater on their Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:836
msgid "Deep Cover Operative"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:840
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Economic Phase. Choose "
"an opponent. You may look through that player's face up Resource Cards "
"(excluding Missions), pick one card, and add it to your hand. Removing a "
"card from a player's face up Resource Cards does not change any of the "
"effects that the card has already generated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:851
msgid ""
"Play when one of your ships enters a Deep Space planet's hex for the "
"first time. The NPAs in this hex will treat you as if your Empire "
"Advantage is Amazing Diplomats for the rest of the game. If your Empire "
"Advantage Card is Amazing Diplomats, then the first time one of your "
"ships goes to that hex place a Colony 5 marker on the planet. Once a "
"player has used either version of Amazing Diplomats to affect a planet, "
"no other player may use either effect on that planet for the rest of the "
"game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:858
msgid "Forced System Shutdown"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:862
msgid ""
"Play during combat, after fleets are revealed but before the first round "
"starts. Select one enemy unit. For the first three battle rounds, treat "
"this unit as not having any Attack, Defense, and Tactics upgrades. If the"
" enemy does not have a spare Group counter, then they have the choice of "
"either destroying the effected ship or having this card effect the entire"
" Group. If played against Replicators, the ship gets –2 to its attack "
"(min of 1) and defense (min of 0), Tactics is not affected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:869
msgid "Smuggler's Route"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:873
msgid ""
"Can be played in one of two ways:\n"
"• At the start of your player turn or the start of an Economic Phase "
"select any unrevealed System marker. Remove the marker from the board.\n"
"• At the start of your player turn, select one Nebula, Asteroid hex, or "
"Black Hole. All your ships that start their movement beside this hex this"
" turn may move through it (provided they have enough movement) without "
"having to stop or having to roll a Black Hole survival check (6.3). This "
"card cannot be combined with a Black Hole Slingshot Maneuver (31.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:882
msgid "Planetary Bombardment"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:886
msgid ""
"Play before bombardment of a Colony starts (5.10). If played by the "
"defender, give +2 to all of the attacker's die rolls. If played by the "
"attacker, give -2 to all their die rolls. Titans are not affected by this"
" card. Transports using Anti-Replicator technology against a Start-level "
"Replicator Colony are not affected by this card (40.2.5)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:893
msgid "Update Your Charts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:897
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Econ Phase. Can be "
"played in one of two ways:\n"
"• Select a hex that is beside an unrevealed Deep Space marker and that "
"does not contain a System marker or a player unit. Add a random Deep "
"Space marker that was set aside at the beginning of the game to that hex."
"\n"
"• Select two unrevealed Deep Space markers and exchange their positions "
"on the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:906
msgid "Play Dead"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:910
msgid ""
"To play this card, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. Play after one of your non-Titan ships is destroyed. "
"Treat this ship as screened for the rest of the battle. It cannot be "
"targeted for the rest of the battle. It cannot fire nor can it retreat. "
"If you win the battle, the ship recovers all damage and rejoins your "
"other ships. If you lose the battle, the enemy will destroy it at no "
"cost. The enemy does get to roll for Experience when they \"kill\" the "
"ship during the battle (37.0). Experience gained by this roll is not lost"
" if the ship survives the battle. This effect cannot be used to save a "
"Missile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:913
msgid "This effect cannot be used to save a Missile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:919
msgid "Overconfidence"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:923
msgid ""
"Play during combat, after fleets are revealed but before the first round "
"starts. Enemy ships in this battle may not retreat (5.9) until one round "
"later than normal (Round 3 for most ships, round 4 if combined with #84 "
"Missed Rendezvous, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:930 app/data/card_manifest.py:1560
msgid "Hidden Power"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:934 app/data/card_manifest.py:1564
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Econ Phase. Immediately"
" draw up to 3 Resource Cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:941
msgid "Sanctions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:945
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn. Choose one opponent, randomly select one "
"Resource Card from their hand (without looking), and place it face up in "
"their discard pile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:952
msgid "Coup"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:956
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Play on a player after a battle where they lost 6+ Hull Points of combat-"
"capable units. In the next Econ Phase, their Homeworld produces half the "
"usual income (round down). The Hull Points must be lost in combat where "
"dice are rolled to take out the ships.\n"
"• Ships lost to Doomsday Machines or Space Amoebas DO count.\n"
"• Bases, Starbases, DSN, and Shipyards DO count.\n"
"• Ships that are captured DO count.\n"
"• Ships lost to Mines DO NOT count.\n"
"• Mines DO NOT count.\n"
"• Ground Units DO NOT count.\n"
"• Missiles DO NOT count.\n"
"For the purpose of counting Hull Points for this card, ignore all special"
" rules, Empire Advantages, and Alien Tech Cards. Count the Hull Points as"
" shown on the counter. In the case of Unique Ships (41.0), count the Hull"
" Size that was paid for. There is no negative effect when played against "
"the Replicators; instead, the player that destroyed the Hull Points has "
"their Homeworld produce 50% greater income (round down) in the next "
"Economic Phase. (Representing a surge in loyalty and hope from getting an"
" important victory.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:971
msgid "Retreat When Engaged"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:975
msgid ""
"Play during a battle before ships are revealed. ALL of your mobile units "
"MUST retreat. This includes Decoys, Mines, Titans, Miners, Colony Ships, "
"Pipelines and your Bases/Shipyards if they can move. If you have a Colony"
" in that space, you may leave as many Fighters or Ground Units as you "
"wish at the Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:982
msgid "Collateral Damage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:986
msgid ""
"Play when a combat-capable unit of either side is destroyed in space "
"combat at a planet. Drop the growth level of the Colony by one level. "
"This cannot cause the Colony to drop below the Colony marker's lowest "
"value, e.g., 0, Start, or 5 (for Homeworlds)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:993 app/data/card_manifest.py:1536
msgid "Minerals +5/–3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:997 app/data/card_manifest.py:1540
msgid ""
"Play at the start of an Economic Phase. Designate one Mineral on a planet"
" or a Miner in a Nebula harvesting resources (34.0) during the Economic "
"Phase. That Mineral/Miner will be worth 5 more or 3 less than normal "
"(your choice – you can either increase your own/teammates' income or "
"decrease your opponents'). If played on Replicators, play this card when "
"the Replicator Player picks up the Mineral."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1004
msgid "Splash Damage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1008
msgid ""
"Play when a combat-capable unit is destroyed in space combat. Deal 1 "
"damage to X other non-screened enemy combat-capable units (including "
"Missiles) in this space battle, where X is the Hull Size of the destroyed"
" ship. For each ship that is damaged by this, roll a die. On a 6-10 they "
"ignore the damage. Titans, Doomsday Machines, Space Amoebas, CVs/BVs "
"protected by Fighters, and Units protected by Shield Projectors cannot be"
" selected as targets of the splash damage. Ships destroyed by Splash "
"Damage do not generate an Experience Roll (37.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1011
msgid "(including Missiles)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1017
msgid "Carthage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1018
msgid ""
"The Barren Planet in each Home System is occupied by a hostile alien "
"race. It is treated like a Deep Space planet, complete with NPAs, drawing"
" Technology Cards, etc. It cannot have the Aggressive Deep Space Planet "
"Attribute. If that attribute is revealed on that planet, discard it, and "
"immediately draw another. Each player cannot explore or enter Deep Space "
"until they defeat these NPAs in their home system. They are the major "
"competing power in your region and must be defeated before conquering the"
" universe."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1024
msgid "Fruitful"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1025
msgid ""
"Barren Planets in a Home System do not need Terraforming to colonize, but"
" are still considered Barren for the purpose of other cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1031
msgid "Worth the Effort"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1032
msgid ""
"If a Colony on a Barren Planet produces any CP, it produces 2 extra CP "
"(or the appropriate type of point if a Facility is present). Do not use "
"(draw another card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1038
msgid "Extinct Alien Empire"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1039
msgid ""
"The Barren Planet in each player's Home System has no NPAs but provides "
"Alien Technology Cards when colonized; Draw 4 cards and keep 2. Do not "
"use (draw another card) if Replicators are in the game. The Xeno-"
"Archeology Resource Card may not be used when colonizing this planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1045
msgid "Expert Empires"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1046
msgid ""
"When drawing Empire Advantage cards, draw 4 and keep 2. Warning – there "
"can be some crazy combinations when playing with this variant, but it is "
"fun."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1052
msgid "No Sensor Lock Possible"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1053
msgid ""
"No combat can occur in Nebulae, all other rules remain the same. It is a "
"neutral space. Both combat and non-combat ships of all players may enter "
"and end their turn in the hex, ignoring the units of other players. "
"Replicators do not gain RPs from enemy units in this hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1059
msgid "Thick Asteroids"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1060
msgid ""
"All other rules for Asteroids are the same, except all ships take one "
"damage in Asteroids. Non-combat ships and ships with one Hull are "
"destroyed; all other ships have one damage on them while in the Asteroids"
" (this is an exception to the rule that only one ship in a group may have"
" damage). They are immediately healed upon exiting Asteroids. This "
"applies to the Space Pilgrims Empire Advantage as well. Missiles cannot "
"be fired in Asteroids. The Insectoids, Giant Race, and Industrious Race "
"Empire Advantages cannot be used if this is in effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1066
msgid "Advanced Navigation"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1067
msgid ""
"Ships do not have to start adjacent in order to enter Asteroids or "
"Nebulae but must still stop upon entering. All other rules are the same."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1073
msgid "Expensive Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1074
msgid ""
"All units except Ground Units cost 1 CP extra to build. For the "
"Replicator player the first 15 CP of Minerals collected provide no "
"income."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1080
msgid "Planetary Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1081
msgid ""
"All planets within 3 hexes are connected by Planetary Gates (see CSB 9.0 "
"but do not place extra Barren Planets at setup)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1087
msgid "A Way Through"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1088
msgid ""
"All rules for Super Novas are the same except they can be entered by "
"specific type(s) of ship, and anything being carried by that ship "
"(Fighters, Ground Units, etc. on board). For that type of ship the Super "
"Nova is like an empty hex. During setup, roll a die: 1-2 SC, 3-4 DD, 5 "
"CA, 6 BC, 7 BB, 8 Raiders, 9 MB & CV & BV, 10 Flagship & Transport. "
"Indicate the result of the roll by placing ship(s) from an unused empire "
"on this card or writing a note on scratch paper. Do not use (draw another"
" card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1094
msgid "Better Homes"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1095
msgid ""
"Home Planets produce 10 CP more if at full strength. The Replicator "
"Homeworld produces 2 extra Hull Points if at full strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1101
msgid "Improved Colony Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1102
msgid ""
"When colonizing a planet (4.4) the colony starts at 1 CP. Bombardment and"
" other game effects can reduce colonies to 0 as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1108
msgid "Close Quarters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1109
msgid ""
"Some ships have lower Weapon classes:\n"
"• DD, CA, Raiders with nullified cloak are E-Class.\n"
"• BC and Fighters are D-Class.\n"
"• BB are C-Class.\n"
"• DN are B-Class.\n"
"These classes can be increased by Alien Tech Cards, Empire Advantages, "
"and other effects. Unique Ships cannot be used. Do not use (draw another "
"card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1120
msgid "Big Ships and Tractor Beams"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1121
msgid ""
"All players start with Ship Size 4. Replicators start with SC/DD/CA "
"already checked off. All players start with Tractor Beams, and all BBs "
"and Type XI Replicator Ships are automatically equipped with them. Do not"
" draw a Special Ability for BBs if using an Alternate Empire; they get "
"this instead. The cost to research Ship Size 7 is 50 CP instead of 30 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1127
msgid "Big Ships and Shield Projectors"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1128
msgid ""
"All players start with Ship Size 5. Replicators start with SC/DD/CA/BC "
"already checked off. All players start with Shield Projectors and all DNs"
" and Type XIIIs Replicator Ships are automatically equipped with them. Do"
" not draw a Special Ability for DNs in an Alternate Empire; they get this"
" instead. The cost to research Ship Size 7 is 60 instead of 30. If the "
"Big Ships and Tractor Beams card is also drawn, each player gets both "
"Tractor Beams and Shield Projectors, but use the higher values for Ship "
"Size, ships checked off, and cost to research Ship Size 7."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1134
msgid "Advanced Destroyers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1135
msgid "All DDs are DDX. Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1141
msgid "Battlecarrier Universica"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1142
msgid ""
"BVs can be built as soon as Fighter 2 tech is researched. Replicators get"
" +1 RP at start. Do not use (draw another card) if an Alternate Empire is"
" in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1148
msgid "Raiders"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1149
msgid ""
"All Raiders are Raider Xs (38.9), but each player gets Scanner 2 for free"
" the moment Scanner 1 is researched (buying Scanner 1 allows you to "
"detect all raiders). NPAs with Scanners still only have Scanner 1. "
"Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1155 app/data/master_rulebook.py:3560
msgid "Advanced Bases"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1156
msgid ""
"All players may build Advanced Bases (38.4) at start. Replicators get +1 "
"RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1162
msgid "Tough Planets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1163
msgid ""
"Planetary Defense Strength from Ground Units present is doubled.\n"
"EXAMPLE: if 4 Ground Units are present, the planet has a Defense Strength"
" of 4 and not 2.\n"
"Ships attacking Replicator colonies get -1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1171
msgid "Tough Shipyards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1172
msgid ""
"All Shipyards, regardless of Empire Advantage, have Hull Size 2 (C3-0-2) "
"and can mount Attack 2 and Defense 2 technology. Maintenance and all "
"other SY rules remain the same. When this is in play, the Empire "
"Advantage On the Move can't be used. Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1178
msgid "Stealth Transports"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1179
msgid ""
"If no type of Base or Defense Satellite Network is present, Ground Units "
"can be landed before resolving space combat or after any round during "
"which the Base or DSN that prevented landing was destroyed. Ion Cannons "
"do not prevent the early landing of Ground Units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1185
msgid "Ion Cannons"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1186
msgid ""
"All player Colonies are equipped with Ion Cannons. Similar to the Militia"
" counter, the Ion Cannon counter is added to the defending force for "
"space combat. There is no penalty for their destruction. They do not "
"benefit from nor provide rolls for experience. A Colony, regardless of "
"size (even a new one), will have 3 Ion Cannons. Even if destroyed, there "
"will be three available at the start of the next combat. These count "
"towards the Fleet Size Bonus and automatically upgrade tech to the limit "
"of their Hull Size (similar to a Base). No maintenance cost needs to be "
"paid for the Ion Cannons and they cannot be boarded. They are A5-0-x1 "
"regardless of Empire Advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1192
msgid "We Need the White"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1193
msgid ""
"At the start of the 6th Econ Phase, each player selects their Home System"
" Colony that is farthest in hexes from their Homeworld. If there is a "
"tie, each player may choose between their own tied colonies. Mark that "
"colony with a Key Planet counter. If that Colony is ever destroyed or "
"captured, that player loses the game (as if they lost their Homeworld)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1199 app/data/game_options.py:282
#: app/data/master_rulebook.py:2908
msgid "Doomsday Machines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1200
msgid ""
"Whenever a Doomsday Machine (29.0) is discovered in Deep Space it attacks"
" the ship that discovered it. If Exploration Technology (9.8) was used, "
"the DM is revealed and placed in the hex with the ship that discovered "
"it; ships in that hex cannot move that turn and no other ships may enter "
"that hex. If the DM survives the battle it will move one hex per turn by "
"the fastest route to attack the Homeworld of the player that discovered "
"it. It will remove planets and Asteroids along the way. If two hexes are "
"equidistant to the Homeworld, determine randomly which one it will enter."
" It will avoid moving into a hex with combat-capable ships and Bases if "
"doing so does not increase the number of hexes to reach the Homeworld. "
"Warning: This drastically changes the game. It is a real danger to "
"explore Deep Space when this is in effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1206 app/data/game_options.py:540
msgid "Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1207
msgid "Play according to the rules for the Space Amoeba scenario (CSB 10.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1213
msgid "Heavy Terrain"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1214
msgid ""
"Place 2 System markers in each Deep Space hex. If there are not enough "
"markers to do this, place them so that they evenly cover rows between the"
" players starting in the center. For example, if there were 6 rows of "
"Deep Space between the players and there was only enough to cover 5 rows,"
" then only the center 4 rows of Deep Space get a second marker. Both are "
"revealed and explored simultaneously (If using Exploration Technology "
"both are looked at simultaneously by one ship and it is not possible to "
"reveal only one marker). If a Super Nova or Fold in Space is revealed, "
"then remove the other marker. If a hex has both a Super Nova and a Fold "
"in Space, remove the Fold in Space. If a Cosmic Storm (25.1) is flipped, "
"remove it if the other marker is something a Storm cannot enter. "
"Otherwise, if there are two permanent terrain markers, they both remain. "
"Use the terrain tile from one of them and put the other counter on top of"
" it.\n"
"EXAMPLE: If an Asteroid and Nebula were revealed in the same hex, then "
"everyone fires as E-Class; there is no Cloak, no Attack Tech, and no "
"Defense Tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1221 app/data/game_options.py:605
msgid "Safer Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1222
msgid ""
"Whenever a Danger! marker is flipped, one die is rolled for each ship in "
"that hex. They are only eliminated on a roll of 7-10. On a roll of 1-6, "
"there is no effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1228 app/data/game_options.py:632
msgid "Smart Scientists"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1229
msgid ""
"The research cost of all technologies is decreased by 5 CP before any "
"Empire Advantage is applied. Replicators also get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1235
msgid "Trained Defenders"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1236
msgid ""
"When invaded, every Colony gets 2 Heavy Infantry Militia in addition to "
"any other Militia or Ground Units from other sources. These two are "
"represented by a separate HI counter and are removed at the end of ground"
" combat, regardless of who wins (All other HI is targeted first i.e. at "
"the end of combat remove 2 HI or 1 if it's the only HI left. No effect if"
" no HI are left at the end of combat). Do not use (draw another card) if "
"Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1242
msgid "Know the Weakness"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1243
msgid ""
"All Unique Ships are equipped with Design Weakness ability. However, "
"instead of giving modifiers against the randomly rolled ship type, the "
"Unique Ships get +2 against the randomly rolled ship type. Roll on the "
"usual table when a UN from a given player first enters combat to "
"determine the ship type. There are no cost savings for Unique Ships "
"having this installed and it does not count towards the other techs they "
"can have installed. The standard version of Design Weakness cannot be "
"chosen when using this Scenario Modifier. Discard and draw another card "
"if not playing with Unique Ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1249
msgid "No Temporal Prime Directive"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1250
msgid ""
"When spending Temporal Points (36.6), everything costs half of normal "
"(rounded up). Discard and draw another card if not playing with "
"Facilities. Beware End of Empire!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1256 app/data/game_options.py:641
msgid "Bloody Combat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1257
msgid "All units except Ground Units have their Attack Strength increased by one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1263
msgid "Experienced Crew"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1264
msgid ""
"At the start of the game, all Players draw 6 Crew Cards (12.0) and keep "
"3. Set them aside. These Crew are held in reserve and not assigned to a "
"group until the player chooses to do so. They can only be assigned to a "
"newly built group during an Economic Phase. No other Crew Cards are used "
"in this game (except if drawn by Resource Card)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1270
msgid "Life is Complicated"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1271
msgid ""
"Discard this card and draw 2 in its place. A total of 3 Scenario Modifier"
" Cards will be in effect for this game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1277 app/data/game_options.py:614
msgid "Rich Minerals"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1278
msgid ""
"The income from all Minerals is doubled. If Minerals +5/-3 is being used "
"to change the value of the Mineral, that change happens before the "
"doubling."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1284
msgid "Technology Head Start"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1285
msgid ""
"Each player starts the game with 75 CP that can only be spent on "
"technology. This is spent before receiving starting units so it is "
"possible that a player's original units may start with additional "
"technology. No more than two levels of Ship Size or Movement tech and no "
"more than one level of any other tech may be purchased at start. Up to 10"
" of these CP may be carried over into the start of the game (and used as "
"normal CP in the game) - if playing with Facilities, these are RP and not"
" CP. Do not use (draw another card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1291
msgid "Low Maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1292
msgid ""
"All maintenance costs are halved. When calculating maintenance, add up "
"the total maintenance cost that you would normally pay (including "
"modifiers from e.g. experience) and then divide it in half (rounded "
"down). When tracking the change in maintenance on the Production Sheet, "
"extra notes will have to be kept on the pre-halved value to prevent "
"having to recount all of your maintenance costs every Economic Phase. If "
"Robot Race is being used, that player would pay no maintenance. Do not "
"use (draw another card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1298
msgid "Where No Man Has Gone Before"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1302
msgid ""
"This card may only be played during your turn. This card may be played "
"face up in front of a player while there are still unexplored Deep Space "
"System markers. Every player's ship with Exploration tech may explore "
"twice each turn. Once every Deep Space System marker is revealed, (only) "
"the player who played this card gets to roll on the Mission Benefit "
"Table."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1309
msgid "Time Travel Slingshot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1313
msgid ""
"Play when one of your CAs performs a Black Hole Slingshot in Deep Space "
"without being destroyed. Leave this card face up. Discard it to reveal "
"all enemy groups/counters in one hex that could be moved into by at least"
" one of your combat-capable ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1320
msgid "Journey to Babel"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1324
msgid ""
"Play when one of your CAs moves by itself into the same hex as an "
"unconquered Deep Space NPA Planet; it has picked up a diplomatic "
"delegation. Instead of a normal battle, one random NPA ship from the "
"planet attacks the CA, which may not retreat. The NPA ship is on a "
"suicide mission and gets +1 attack and defense. Regardless of the "
"outcome, the NPA ship is eliminated. Any other NPA ships at that planet "
"will not attack the CA. The CA must leave the hex next turn. If the CA "
"defeats the ship and reaches its Homeworld, in the following Economic "
"Phase the NPA Planet (if still unconquered) becomes allies to that player"
" as if they had the Empire Advantage Amazing Diplomats. Place a 5 CP "
"colony on that planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1331
msgid "Balance of Terror"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1335
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select one other player. The two players each "
"select one of their ships (a Group may be split to facilitate this) "
"located in Deep Space, regardless of each ship's location in relation to "
"one another. If a player has no ships in Deep Space, they may choose any "
"one of their ships. If the ship can carry fighters and has fighters in "
"the same hex, up to the amount of fighters the ship may carry are chosen "
"too. These two chosen units then have an immediate battle to the death in"
" open space with no possibility of retreat. The winner of this battle may"
" attack a hex with a colony belonging to a player involved in the battle "
"(not a Homeworld) with the chosen units regardless of location. After the"
" attack and any possible bombardment, the units are returned to their "
"previous hex if they survive. The Temporal Engine Benefit Temporal "
"Maneuver may not be used during this Mission."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1342
msgid "Creature from Below"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1346
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select a non-Homeworld Colony in a Home System, "
"friendly or enemy, and place the Creature token (A5-2-x4, 3 attacks each "
"round) on it. This Creature does no damage to the planet, but the Colony "
"is treated as if it is blockaded until the Creature is defeated in ground"
" combat (Militia do not participate). Troops on the same planet must "
"attack the Creature during their owner's next combat phase. If the "
"Creature defeats the Troops, all damage to it is healed and the Colony is"
" still considered blockaded. When it is defeated, that player gets a one-"
"time bonus of 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1353
msgid "Arena"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1357
msgid ""
"Play at the start of a battle involving exactly one ship of each side. An"
" advanced entity stops the battle and decides it is more civilized to "
"have the captains of each ship fight to the death (how that is actually "
"more advanced or civilized is unclear). Regardless of the ships involved,"
" the player that played the card wins the battle on a roll of 1-6, their "
"opponent on a roll of 7-10. The ship on the losing side is destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1364
msgid "Difficult Planet Survey"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1368
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select any planet without a Colony or NPAs and "
"mark it with the Difficult Survey counter. This planet is difficult to "
"settle. Every time at least one CA or Flagship ends its turn in the "
"planet's hex, roll a die. On a roll of a 1-2, the marker is taken by the "
"owner of the ships, and the planet may be colonized. If the colony is "
"placed by the player with the counter they draw 1 Alien Tech card and "
"keep it. This is in addition to any other Alien Tech drawn for colonizing"
" the planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1375
msgid "Easy Planet Survey"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1379
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select any planet without a colony or Non-Player "
"Aliens and mark it with the Easy Survey counter. It cannot be colonized "
"unless 2 SCs are in the same hex at the time the Colony Ship lands. When "
"colonized, this planet will grow 2 steps (instead of 1) during the next "
"Economic Phase, then remove the counter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1386
msgid "Scientific Survey"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1390
msgid ""
"Play this card face up when one of your CAs is adjacent to a Super Nova. "
"Turn the CA face up. If this CA subsequently moves adjacent to 2 other "
"Super Novas, discard this card and roll on the Mission Benefit Table. If "
"the player turns the CA face down at a Colony or if it is destroyed, "
"discard this card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1397
msgid "Stellar Anomaly Investigation"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1401
msgid ""
"Play this card face up when you have 2 of your combat ships of different "
"types in the same Deep Space hex containing at least one Nebula marker. "
"Turn those ships face up. At the end of each turn (including this one), "
"roll the die. On a roll of 1-3, discard this card and roll on the Mission"
" Benefit Table. If one or both ships leave the hex discard this card for "
"no effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1408
msgid "Distress Call"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1412
msgid ""
"Play when a ship you control is eliminated in battle. Instead of being "
"destroyed, it is placed in a hex adjacent to the battle that is farther "
"from your Homeworld than the battle hex (your choice). The chosen hex "
"must contain one or more unexplored system markers if possible. When this"
" hex is explored, remove and ignore the system markers. The player cannot"
" move this ship until the turn after another of their ships ends their "
"turn in the hex, but the ship may defend itself normally. This card may "
"be played on a ship that had the Play Dead Resource Card played on it if "
"you lose the battle and that ship is going to be destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1419
msgid "Quell Riots"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1423
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select a non-Homeworld Colony in a Home System, "
"friendly or enemy, and mark it with the Riot counter. While the counter "
"is at the Colony it is considered blockaded. If at least 4 Hull Points "
"worth of combat-capable units except Shipyards, any Bases, and Defense "
"Satellite Networks belonging to the Colony's owner end their move at that"
" Colony that player rolls a die (reveal all combat-capable units involved"
" to prove it):\n"
"• 1-5 – Remove Riot counter and roll twice on the Mission Benefit Table. "
"The counter remains until this result is rolled.\n"
"• 6-8 – No effect.\n"
"• 9-10 – Reduce Colony one step. This can reduce the Colony to start, but"
" never destroy it.\n"
"If less than 4 Hull Points worth of ships are at the Colony during an "
"Economic Phase, roll the die but there is only an effect on 9-10 as per "
"above. This counts any modifiers to hull size, e.g. Giant Race and "
"Insectoids."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1434
msgid "Police State"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1438
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select a Deep Space Colony, friendly or enemy, and"
" mark it with the Police State counter. Very valuable resources have been"
" discovered on this planet, but the indigenous population does not want "
"to make them available. The Colony is considered blockaded unless the "
"owner has at least 4 Space Marines and/or Heavy Infantry and 6 Hull "
"Points of combat-capable units (including Bases, Shipyards, DSN) revealed"
" in that hex (This counts any modifiers to hull size, e.g. Giant Race and"
" Insectoids). If they do, the Colony produces 10 additional CP that "
"Economic Phase. If playing with Facilities (36.0), the additional income "
"is always CP regardless of the Facility present. As soon as less than "
"required units are present the colony is considered blockaded again."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1445
msgid "New FTL Test"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1449
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Reveal a ship with at least 2 Hull Points in Deep "
"Space in a hex with no other ships. It must have the highest level of "
"Movement Technology that you have researched. The Technology Level does "
"not need to be revealed. Roll a die one time:\n"
"• 1-7 – The test is a success! The next Movement technology purchased is "
"discounted by 15 CP.\n"
"• 8-9 – The test fails.\n"
"• 10 – Calamity! The test ship is destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1459
msgid "Dimensional Anomaly"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1463
msgid ""
"Play during your Exploration Phase when a CA is your only ship (not "
"Group) in a hex that had a system marker explored by that CA this phase "
"(after resolving any system marker effects, including combat against "
"NPAs) The CA is then shifted to another dimension and is removed from the"
" board. At the beginning of each Economic Phase, roll a die. On 1-3, the "
"CA is placed back on the board at a friendly Base or Shipyard. Subtract 2"
" from the die roll for each successive Econ Phase (e.g., in the third "
"Econ Phase it would be -4 to the roll). The CA does not pay maintenance "
"while off board. Roll on Mission Benefit Table when it returns to the "
"board. System marker may have been previously peeked at (but not "
"flipped), using Exploration technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1470
msgid "Asteroid Strike"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1474
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Place the Rogue Asteroid counter in an Asteroid "
"hex and place the Asteroid Target counter in the same hex as an enemy "
"non-Homeworld Colony at least two hexes away. Each Economic Phase the "
"Rogue Asteroid moves one hex closer to the Colony (your choice if two "
"hexes are equidistant). If it enters the same hex as the Colony, remove "
"both the Colony and the Rogue Asteroid. If any player ends the movement "
"phase in the same hex as the Rogue Asteroid with ships that have a "
"combined Attack Strength of 3 or more (not counting attack technology), "
"the player may remove the Rogue Asteroid counter (being in a hex when the"
" Rogue Asteroid moves into the hex is not sufficient). Boarding Ships "
"count as having an Attack Strength of 1 for this, Missile Boats count as "
"having an Attack Strength of 6. If the units in the hex do not have a "
"combined total of at least 3 Attack Strength, nothing happens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1481
msgid "Urgent Deep Space Survey"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1485
msgid ""
"Play when one of your ships that is worth 12+ CP ends its turn in one of "
"the following types of terrain in Deep Space – Nebula, Asteroids, Black "
"Hole, Warp Point, Plasma Storm, Ion Storm, Quantum Filament, Quasar, or "
"Pulsar. The ship must then subsequently end its turn in 3 more of the "
"listed terrain types (it must be different hexes, but not necessarily "
"different terrain types) and then get back to one of your Colonies that "
"has a Shipyard, Base, or Starbase. If successful, roll on the Mission "
"Benefit Table. The ship performing this Mission must be revealed when the"
" card is played. You may use your Flagship to complete this mission. If "
"the designated ship is destroyed or the ship is flipped face down, "
"discard this card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1492
msgid "Survivors"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1496
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. A shuttle containing one of your enemy's people "
"(choose an opponent at random) has crash-landed on a revealed but "
"uncolonized NPA planet (choose randomly). Mark the planet with a counter "
"from that Empire. If you colonize the planet while it has the counter you"
" capture the survivors and ransom them back for 10 CP (gained by you as "
"if it was mineral income and lost by that enemy during the next Economic "
"Phase) and get to look at the technology portion of that Empire's "
"Production Sheet (immediately) and the counter is removed. If another "
"player colonizes this planet, the counter is removed without any effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1503
msgid "Sins of the Father"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1507
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select one of your ships of Hull Size 2 or greater"
" in a Deep Space hex. A crew member from that ship must resolve a "
"familial dispute on your Homeworld. If this ship begins and ends a turn "
"at the Homeworld, draw a Crew Card (12.0). Do this even if not playing "
"with Crew Cards. The Crew Card must be played as normal during the next "
"Economic Phase or is discarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1514
msgid "Defend an Outpost"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1518
msgid ""
"Play at the end of your turn. Choose one of your own non-Homeworld Deep "
"Space Colonies. The opponent of your choice MUST immediately attack it "
"with between 2 and 10 of their Ground Units (if possible). These Ground "
"Units can be taken from anywhere on the board, including Transports, and "
"are instantly placed on the planet and may fire normally during the first"
" round (unlike normal rules, 21.8.3). The defender does not get Militia. "
"There is no space battle, but all units in the hex are revealed. If the "
"attacker wins, they may decide to capture this Colony by removing one "
"surviving Ground Unit as normal. If the defender (the person that played "
"the card) wins the attack, they roll on the Mission Benefit Table. If the"
" player chosen does not have at least 2 Ground Units, no attack takes "
"place, and the defender gets to roll on the Mission Benefit Table."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1547
msgid "Privateers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1551
msgid ""
"Can be played for one of two effects:\n"
"• Play when peeking at a Space Pirate using Exploration Technology or "
"Regional Map to hire that Space Pirate as if the counter was revealed "
"during the Exploration Phase. In the case of using Exploration "
"technology, the Space Pirate is hired before movement and may therefore "
"be moved under the player's control that turn.\n"
"• Play when revealing a Space Pirate during the Exploration Phase while "
"already in control of a Space Pirate to ignore the restriction and hire "
"the newly revealed Space Pirate as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1571
msgid "Virus"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1575
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select any non-Homeworld Colony. Place a Virus "
"counter on it. In the next Economic Phase, that Colony is treated as if "
"it is blockaded. Remove the counter at the end of that Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1582
msgid "Sabotage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1586
msgid ""
"Play at the beginning of your first turn after an Economic Phase. A "
"player of your choice must destroy one Defense Satellite Network or any "
"type of Base of their own choice. Replicators must destroy one ship not "
"in their Home System. If the player does not have one of those, then this"
" card is discarded for no effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1593
msgid "Population +/-"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1597
msgid ""
"Play during an Economic Phase after adjusting Colony income. Choose one "
"non-Homeworld Colony. That Colony either grows an extra level or goes "
"down one level. This cannot cause a Colony to be eliminated but can "
"reduce it to 0."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1604
msgid "Self-Sustaining Power Source"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1605
msgid "Titans pay 1/2 maintenance (round down the total)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1612
msgid "Advanced Shipyards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1613
msgid ""
"Shipyards produce an extra half Hull Point each. (1.5 at level one, 2 at "
"level 2, 2.5 at level three.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1620
msgid "Lorelei System"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1621
msgid ""
"Allows a player to designate their SC, SCX, DD, and DDX as the target of "
"Mines that were not swept after technology was revealed in combat "
"(17.1.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1628
msgid "Ancient Weapons Cache"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1629
msgid ""
"In the following Economic Phase, the player gains 2 Cyber Armor (38.7) at"
" one of their Colonies even if they do not have the appropriate "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1631
msgid "When any Cyber Armor is revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1636
msgid "Quantum Computing"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1637
msgid ""
"All of this player's Unique Ships may now mount a 3rd Unique Technology "
"and they no longer pay 5 CP to redesign UNs. Immediately add a 3rd tech "
"to your current UN design (do not change any other aspect). All UNs "
"currently on the board gain this third tech (at your current tech level "
"if applicable) at no cost."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1639
msgid "When gained."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1644
msgid "Focused Phasers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1645
msgid "Unique Ships get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1647 app/data/card_manifest.py:2118
#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2126
msgid "When a UN is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1652
msgid "Skipper Missiles"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1653
msgid "All Missiles (24.4) strike their targets as C-Class instead of E-Class."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1655
msgid "When a MB is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1660
msgid "War Sun"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1661
msgid ""
"This race has spent generations refitting an ancient warship, and it is "
"nearly operational. Once during the game, they gain a free Titan at their"
" Homeworld. It will have the player's current tech and requires no "
"Shipyard to place. It pays no maintenance as long as it is at a friendly "
"Colony during the Econ Phase. This ship may not enter Deep Space until "
"Ship Size 6 has been researched. Additionally, the War Sun has revealed "
"to this race the ability to pass safely through Super Nova hexes (though "
"they cannot end their movement in one). Alternate Empires (24.0) are "
"given one Titan counter. This is the only time an Alternate Empire can "
"have a Titan; they may still not research or build other Titans and they "
"may not rebuild this one if destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1663
msgid "This ship may not enter Deep Space until Ship Size 6 has been researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1665
msgid "When any of their Titan counters are revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1670
msgid "Salvage Experts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1671
msgid ""
"When this race wins a space battle, they may salvage one friendly "
"destroyed combat ship (not Shipyards, Bases, Mines, Starbases, Defense "
"Satellite Networks, or Flagships). The salvaged ship is placed face down "
"in the hex at its previous Ship Experience level. Ships that were "
"carrying other units or Logistic Points when they were destroyed do not "
"regain them when the ship is salvaged. If none of their ships are "
"destroyed no ship is gained, but if the enemy lost at least one combat "
"ship, this empire gains 3 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1673
msgid "When first entering combat, including Aliens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1678
msgid "Berserker Genome"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1679
msgid ""
"At the end of every combat round of space combat in which this race loses"
" a unit, they may make a special attack for each unit destroyed (units "
"hit by boarding attacks do not count as destroyed for this purpose). "
"These bonus attacks hit on a roll of 1+the Hull Size of the destroyed "
"unit, regardless of the target's defense and does one damage (example: a "
"destroyed BC gets a final attack hitting on 1-3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1686
msgid "Robot Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1687
msgid ""
"Due to the low maintenance of this race, all maintenance is halved; add "
"up all maintenance costs (including reductions from alien technology "
"cards and experience), divide the total in half and round down."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1694
msgid "Masters of the Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1695
msgid ""
"All CAs have Warp Gates without any research and at no extra cost. Rules "
"as per UN Ship Table #3."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1697
msgid "The first time a Warp Gate is used or a CA is in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1702
msgid "Mycroft"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1703
msgid ""
"Natural attack rolls of \"1\" by ships in this Group grant the attacking "
"ship a second attack roll (these may be against the same or different "
"Groups). If on a ship with Hull Size of 1, the second attack roll is "
"granted on rolls of 1-2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1709
msgid "Hive Queen"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1710
msgid ""
"This Group gets +1 Defense Strength. All OTHER Replicator Groups in the "
"fleet get +1 Attack Strength and -1 Defense Strength. This is not "
"optional!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1716
msgid "Hal 10K"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1717
msgid ""
"This Group fires at its normal Weapon class, regardless of terrain. "
"Movement Rules are unaffected by this."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1723
msgid "Rommie"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1724
msgid ""
"Every time a ship in this Group suffers a hit, roll a die. On a roll of "
"1, the hit is ignored."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1730
msgid "WOPR"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1731
msgid ""
"Once per round, this Group may reroll one Attack die or choose one Attack"
" die against the Group to be rerolled. The decision must be made "
"immediately after the die is rolled. The first result is undone and the "
"second roll must be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1737
msgid "Data"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1738
msgid ""
"During movement only, this Group ignores Asteroids, Nebulae, and Black "
"Holes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1744
msgid "Skynet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1745
msgid ""
"During the first round of combat only, this Group and 2 others of the "
"Replicator player's choice fight as one Weapon Class higher."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1751
msgid "Quorra"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1752
msgid ""
"This Group cannot be targeted by Mines as if equipped with Anti-Sensor "
"Hull."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1758
msgid "Agent Smith"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1759
msgid ""
"This fleet gets a Fleet Size Bonus when it has at least one more combat-"
"capable ship than the opponent. The opposing fleet does not get a Fleet "
"Size Bonus unless this Crew Card's fleet is outnumbered by 3:1. If the "
"opposing fleet is Expert Tacticians or has an Admiral of the Navy (or "
"both), everything cancels each other out and the Fleet Size Bonus is "
"given at 2:1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1765
msgid "Ash"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1766
msgid ""
"In each combat, choose one hex into which the enemy cannot retreat. The "
"decision of which hex is forbidden is made when an enemy Group announces "
"intent to retreat for the first time and applies to all enemy retreats in"
" that combat. The restriction is immediately lifted if this Group is "
"destroyed or retreats. The Group may be screened and still take advantage"
" of this effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1772
msgid "Alexa"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1773
msgid ""
"This Group's Movement technology operates as if it was one level higher "
"than currently installed, even if that higher level has not been "
"researched. It can't operate at a level above the maximum of Movement 7."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1779
msgid "Sonny"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1780 app/data/card_manifest.py:1817
msgid ""
"One ship in this Group gets +1 to Attack Strength. If on a Group with a "
"Hull Size of 1, it gets +2 and ignores the first hit against it in "
"combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1786
msgid "Governor"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1787
msgid ""
"The Group gets 2 attacks in the first combat round only. If on a Flagship"
" or Titan, this applies to all combat rounds. If on a Titan, each hit "
"from the Group also does 3 Damage, but every time a ship in the Group is "
"hit by a fighter, roll a die. On a roll of 10 a Titan is destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1793
msgid "Security Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1794
msgid ""
"Regardless of whether the Security Officer survives, all friendly crew in"
" the same Fleet as this officer get -2 to all survival rolls. All ships "
"in the Group get +1 defense against Boarding Ships. If on a Flagship, "
"select one additional Group at the beginning of combat that will receive "
"this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1796
msgid ""
"all friendly crew in the same Fleet as this officer get -2 to all "
"survival rolls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1802
msgid "Damage Control Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1803
msgid ""
"If this Group has any damage, after each round of combat it may attempt "
"repairs. On a roll of a 1 or less, repair all damage. On a roll of a 2-5,"
" repair 1 Damage. If on the Flagship or a BB, subtract 2 from the die "
"roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1809
msgid "Ensign Expendable"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1810
msgid "This Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1816
msgid "Hero"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1823
msgid "Engineer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1824
msgid ""
"This Group's Movement Tech operates at one level higher than currently "
"installed, even if that higher level has not been researched. It can't "
"operate at a level above the maximum of 7."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1830
msgid "Asteroid Navigator"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1831
msgid ""
"This Group can ignore Asteroids when moving. If playing with Thick "
"Asteroids, this Group does not take damage from the Asteroids. If on a "
"SC, DD, or Flagship, it also ignores Black Holes (unless using "
"Slingshot)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1837
msgid "Nebula Navigator"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1838
msgid ""
"This Group can ignore Nebulae when moving. If on a SC, DD, or the "
"Flagship, it may also ignore Black Holes (unless using Slingshot, 31.0). "
"If on a MB, it also ignores Asteroids when moving."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1844
msgid "Helmsmen"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1845
msgid ""
"This Group may fire and then immediately retreat in the same round (they "
"may still not retreat on round 1 unless permitted by some other effect). "
"If on a Raider, the Group may also fire and retreat in round 1. The group"
" retreats prior to any other effects e.g. Splash Damage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1851
msgid "Supply Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1852
msgid ""
"Each ship in the Group pays 1 less maintenance. This is applied prior to "
"any other reductions due to experience, alien technologies, empire "
"advantages, etc."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1858
msgid "Defender"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1859
msgid ""
"Once per battle, after the first round, at the start of a round, this "
"Group may announce that it is setting its defenses to \"Area Mode.\" For "
"that round, or until all ships in this Group are destroyed, all attacks "
"against other friendly Groups suffer an additional penalty equal to the "
"defense technology of the Defender Group (if in a Nebula, this would be "
"zero). However, attacks against the Defender Group suffer no penalty due "
"to its defense technology. This may be used even if the Group is "
"screened. If on a BC, this benefit may be used in the first round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1865
msgid "Tactician"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1866
msgid ""
"After the first round, during a single round of combat, if your fleet in "
"the combat contains Groups of at least three different Hull Sizes, your "
"ships gain +1 Attack or +1 Defense for the round. This bonus is "
"determined at the start of the round and stays in effect even if all "
"ships of one hull size are destroyed partway through the round. If on a "
"BB or DN, this benefit may be used in the first round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1872
msgid "Strategist"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1873
msgid ""
"Once in each combat, choose four enemy ships (not Groups) and decide "
"which one of your Groups they will fire against in that round. If that "
"Group is destroyed, they are free to choose their next target. The "
"designated Group must be a legal target (not a CV with Fighters, etc.). "
"If on a SC, DD, CA, or MB, six enemy ships may be chosen in that round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1879
msgid "First Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1880
msgid ""
"This Group gets +2 to its Tactics level (to a max of 3). If on an SC or a"
" DD, this Group also improves its Weapon Class by one letter, even in "
"terrain (SC would fire as D-Class in Asteroids, etc.). This is in "
"addition to any other benefits like Longbowmen or Long Lance Torpedo. If "
"on the Flagship, this ship always fires or retreats before all other "
"ships in the combat, regardless of technology or terrain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1886
msgid "Tactical Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1887
msgid ""
"Once during each battle, this ship (not Group) may fire (or retreat if "
"eligible) as A-Class, even in terrain. If on an SC or DD this applies to "
"the entire Group. All ships in the Group get +1 to defense against "
"boarding. If on a Flagship, this applies to one other group as well."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1893
msgid "Captain"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1894
msgid ""
"May reroll one attack from the Group or have one attack against it "
"rerolled once per combat round. The decision must be made immediately "
"after the die is rolled. The first result is undone and the second roll "
"must be used. If on an SC, DD, CA, or MB, it may reroll 2 attacks per "
"round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1900
msgid "Weapons Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1901
msgid ""
"Natural attack rolls of 1 by ships in this Group grant the attacking ship"
" a second attack roll (against the same or a different Group as the first"
" attack). If on an SC, DD, Raider, or Flagship, the second attack roll is"
" granted on 1 or 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1907
msgid "Heavy Weapons Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1908
msgid ""
"All ships in this Group do 2 damage every time they hit a Colony, any "
"type of Base, Shipyard, or Defense Satellite Network."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1914
msgid "Science Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1915
msgid ""
"This Group cannot be targeted by Mines in the same way as Anti-Sensor "
"Hull. If on a SW, this Group also sweeps one more Mine per ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1921
msgid "Marine Captain"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1922
msgid ""
"The Group can carry one extra Ground Unit total even if it normally could"
" not carry Ground Units. If on a CA, each ship in the Group can carry one"
" Ground Unit. If on a Flagship, the Group may carry 4 Ground Units total."
" Ships in the Group carrying Ground Units cannot be boarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1928
msgid "Planetary Admiral"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1929
msgid ""
"Group gets +1 Attack Strength if fighting in a hex with a planet. If on a"
" BB, DN, or Titan, all ships in the fleet get this bonus."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1935
msgid "Admiral of the Navy"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1936
msgid ""
"This fleet gets a Fleet Size Bonus when it has at least one more combat-"
"capable ship than the opponent. The opposing fleet does not get a Fleet "
"Size Bonus unless this Crew Card's fleet is outnumbered by 3:1. If the "
"opposing fleet is Expert Tacticians or has an Admiral of the Navy (or any"
" combination thereof), everything cancels each other out and the Fleet "
"Size Bonus is given at 2:1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1942
msgid "Fleet Admiral"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1943
msgid ""
"This Group and 2 others get +1 Attack on the first round of combat only. "
"If on a Titan, then one additional Group gets this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1949
msgid "Admiral"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1950
msgid ""
"This Group and 2 others fight as one Weapon Class higher for the first "
"round of combat only. If on a DN, then one additional Group gets this "
"benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1956
msgid "Commander"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1957
msgid ""
"If this fleet has more ships than the opponent, it can designate one "
"Group in this fleet that cannot be shot at the first round unless all "
"other ships are destroyed (i.e., for target selection treat one Group as "
"if they were a Carrier with unscreened fighters the first round). If on a"
" BB, then one additional Group gets this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1963
msgid "Rear Admiral"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1964
msgid ""
"This Group and 1 other have their Defense Strength increased by one for "
"the first round of combat only. If on a DN, then one additional Group "
"gets this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1970
msgid "General Staff"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1971
msgid ""
"In each combat, this Crew can choose one hex that the enemy can't retreat"
" into as long as the General Staff's Group is in the combat. The decision"
" of which hex is forbidden is made when an enemy Group announces intent "
"to retreat for the first time and applies to all enemy retreats in that "
"combat. The restriction is immediately lifted if this Group is destroyed "
"or retreats. The Group may be screened and still take advantage of this "
"effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1977
msgid "Ordnance Technician/ECCM Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1978
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, all Fighters in the same fleet that would fire as "
"B-Class fire instead as A-Class. If on an MB, when this Group fires on "
"CAs with Jamming Technology, the Missiles ignore all jamming. On any "
"Group other than CV, BV or MB, this Crew Card can be discarded to cancel "
"one hit against the Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1984
msgid "Warrant Officer/ECCM Specialist"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1985
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, ships in this Group can carry 1 extra Fighter each. If "
"on an MB, all ships in this Group may fire ECCM Missiles instead of using"
" their normal attack. These Missiles do no damage and do not attack enemy"
" ships. For each ship that fires ECCM Missiles each round, two Missiles "
"fired by other MBs ignore all jamming. On any Group other than CV, BV or "
"MB, this Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1991
msgid "Squadron Leader"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1992
msgid ""
"Ships in this Group get +1 Attack Strength. If on a Fighter, the ships in"
" this Group also get +1 Defense Strength and fire as A-Class (regardless "
"of terrain)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1998
msgid "CAG"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:1999
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, one Group of Fighters in the fleet fires as A-Class and"
" gets +1 Attack Strength each round, regardless of terrain. A different "
"Group may be chosen each round. On any group other than CV or BV, this "
"Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2005
msgid "Deck Crew Chief"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2006
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, at the end of a round of combat, roll a die. On a roll "
"of a 1-4, one friendly Fighter that was destroyed that round is returned "
"to service (no benefit if no fighter was destroyed that round). If on a "
"BV, subtract 3 from the roll. If playing with Experience, the Fighters "
"that are returned are Skilled. On any group other than CV or BV, this "
"Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2012
msgid "Gunnery Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2013
msgid ""
"Group fires at its normal Weapon Class regardless of terrain. If on a BC,"
" this applies to one other Group as well."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2019
msgid "Commodore"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2020
msgid ""
"At the start of combat select one enemy Group. This Group cannot split "
"and cannot retreat until round 3. If on a BB, this applies to all "
"opposing Groups."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2026
msgid "Marine Commander"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2027
msgid ""
"If on a Transport, this Group can drop Ground Units before space combat "
"starts when attacking another player (not NPAs). Ground combat is still "
"resolved after Space combat. On any group other than Transport, this Crew"
" Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against his Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2033
msgid "Marine Lieutenant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2034
msgid ""
"A Transport with this Crew Card has \"Suppressing Fire\": if this Group "
"is present in a hex where there is ground combat, pick one type of enemy "
"unit. All enemy units of that type get -2 Attack Strength on the first "
"round of ground combat. On any other ship this Crew Card can be discarded"
" to cancel one hit against this group (this discard effect cannot be used"
" on a Transport)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2040
msgid "Special Warfare Technician"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2041
msgid ""
"This Group's Point Defense, Cloaking, Scanners, Mine Sweeping, Boarding, "
"Exploration, Missile Boat, or Jammer technologies operate as if they were"
" one level higher than currently installed, even if that technology has "
"not been researched. It cannot operate at a level above the maximum.\n"
"EXAMPLE: A Raider with Cloaking 2 gets no benefit from this Crew Card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2048
msgid "Chief Engineer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2049
msgid "This Group gets instant technology upgrades, just like Bases or Shipyards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2055
msgid "Patrol Leader"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2056
msgid ""
"If a Group with this Crew Card spends its entire time between Economic "
"Phases on MS Pipelines that connect Colonies, the player gets an "
"additional 3 CP in the next Economic Phase. If this Crew Card is on a DD,"
" the player gets an additional 5 CP instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2062
msgid "Astrometrics Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2063
msgid ""
"Once per Economic Phase, immediately before new ships are placed, the "
"player may peek at one face down Group belonging to another player within"
" one hex of the Group with this Crew Card. The Group remains face down "
"after peeking. If this Crew Card is on a CA, it may peek at a Group "
"within three hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2069
msgid "Operations Officer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2070
msgid ""
"Once between Economic Phases, the Group with this Crew Card may do one of"
" the following:\n"
"• Ignore the movement effect of one (and only one) hex containing Nebula,"
" Asteroids, Quantum Filament, Plasma Storm, or a Black Hole (survival is "
"automatic, but may not use Black Hole Slingshot).\n"
"• All ships on this Group get either +1 Attack Strength or +1 Defense "
"Strength for one round.\n"
"Turn this Crew Card sideways to show that it has been used and return it "
"to vertical in the next Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2079
msgid "Weak NPAs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2080
msgid ""
"All deep space Barren planets have one less ship and one less Heavy "
"Infantry (minimum 0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2086
msgid "Hardy Empires"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2087
msgid "All Empires start with Terraforming 1. Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2094
msgid ""
"CAs are automatically equipped with Second Salvo at no extra cost as per "
"the Unique Ship Rules. Prior to Economic Phase 8 Flagships are treated as"
" having Second Salvo while in combat in the Home System of their owner. "
"After Economic Phase 8, they are automatically and permanently equipped "
"with it. Do not use (draw another card) if Replicators are in the game. "
"Do not use Cloaking Geniuses if this card is in play."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2100
msgid "Recon Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2101
msgid ""
"In addition to the normal starting forces, each player receives 6 Recon "
"Ships (use Unique Ship counters). They are E1-0 x1, but cost no "
"maintenance. They may be upgraded, but not built. Do not use the normal "
"UN rules. If a player draws Alien Tech Cards 282 or 283, the player may "
"remove any remaining Recon Ships in order to build the new design, but "
"may not build other designs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2107
msgid "Bioweapons"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2108
msgid ""
"All DDs are instantly upgraded to have Bioweapons. They automatically hit"
" when bombarding a planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2115
msgid "Aegis Frigate"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2116
msgid ""
"You have the plans to build Aegis Frigates (use Unique Ship counters). "
"They are E1-3 x2 and are equipped with Shield Projectors (regardless of "
"whether they have been researched). They cost 11 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2123
msgid "War Frigate"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/card_manifest.py:2124
msgid ""
"You have the plans to build War Frigates (use Unique Ship counters). They"
" are E5-1 x2 and have Design Weakness). They cost 10 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:8
msgid "Aggressive"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:12
msgid ""
"Immediately reveal all NPA ships in this hex when the counter is flipped."
" These ships attack units that end their move in an adjacent hex, then "
"instantly move back to their own planet afterwards. During any combat "
"phase Aggressive NPAs will defend against attacks on their own planet "
"first, then will attack units in adjacent hexes one by one (choose the "
"order randomly if multiple hexes eligible, colony hexes last, see below) "
"until they are destroyed or no enemy units remain in eligible adjacent "
"hexes. These attacks do not trigger Reaction Movement (35.0). Aggressive "
"NPAs will never attack units in home systems or Thick Asteroids. They "
"will also not attack NPAs except ones captured by players (they will "
"attack solo Alien Empire opponent units). They will only attack units in "
"hexes with deep space colonies once no units remain in hexes without "
"colonies. If the defending units are destroyed any colony is "
"automatically destroyed too without bombardment. Aggressive NPAs do not "
"cause mines to be detonated (this is an exception to 17.1.4); however, "
"they lose this feature if they are captured or join Amazing Diplomats. If"
" all Aggressive NPA ships are destroyed while in a hex adjacent to their "
"own planet, randomly draw one NPA ship and place it on their planet, this"
" ship will not perform any more attacks until the next combat phase. This"
" Attribute is removed when the planet is colonized."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:17
msgid "Spice"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:21
msgid ""
"This planet can only be taken via Ground Combat (21.8); it can never be "
"colonized with a Colony Ship. If an attempt to take this planet fails, "
"the next invasion force will again face 4 Heavy Infantry and 5 Militia. "
"Once conquered by a player, future invasions will only need to defeat "
"that player's Ground Units (without the replenished Heavy Infantry). If a"
" player's Colony is destroyed by bombardment, the now empty planet will "
"once again be guarded by 4 HI and 5 Militia. If a full-strength Colony is"
" at the end of an Economic Phase, all that player's ships (in supply, "
"36.5) move at a rate 1 technology level higher until the next Economic "
"Phase. Replicators (40.0) also receive this benefit. If a Replicator "
"Colony is removed from this planet, remove this Attribute."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:26
msgid "Organia"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:30
msgid ""
"This planet cannot be conquered, colonized, or connected to a player's "
"trade network (13.2.2). No combat can occur in this planet's hex, but it "
"may be moved or retreated into even if enemy ships are present in the "
"hex. Treat this space as a Galactic Capitol (28.1) for purposes of "
"movement restrictions. Because combat is forbidden, Replicators do not "
"gain RPs from other ships in this hex, even for encountering an NPA "
"(18.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:35
msgid "Dilithium Crystals"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:39
msgid ""
"At the end of every Economic Phase during which there is a full-strength "
"Colony on this planet, place a Dilithium counter on the planet if there "
"isn't one already (if all Dilithium counters are already on the map no "
"additional one is placed). The player who owns this Colony may use a "
"Transport (21.1) to carry one counter (and nothing else) to their "
"Homeworld. If successfully transported, the Dilithium counter provides a "
"number of CP equal to the distance from this planet to the Homeworld. Use"
" the shortest possible route when calculating distance, taking into "
"effect Warp Points (28.2) and Folds in Space (25.2) but not Warp Gates. "
"If Replicators grow a Colony on this planet to full-strength, they remove"
" this Attribute and gain 10 CP. If a player's Colony on this planet is "
"conquered or destroyed (including if a Titan destroys the planet), any "
"existing Dilithium counters carried by that player's Transports which "
"originated from this planet may still provide CP upon arrival to their "
"Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:44
msgid "Abundant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:48
msgid ""
"This planet produces 2 extra CP each Economic Phase during which there is"
" a Colony here, even if the Colony is new. Replicators treat this as "
"Mineral CP (40.6.1)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:53
msgid "Wealthy"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:57
msgid ""
"This planet produces 1 extra CP each Economic Phase during which there is"
" a Colony here, even if the Colony is new. If a Replicator Colony is "
"placed here, remove this Attribute (the wealth comes from the native "
"economy; Replicators would ignore it)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:62
msgid "Poor"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:66
msgid ""
"This planet produces 1 less CP each Economic Phase during which there is "
"a Colony here, to a minimum of 0. If a Replicator Colony is placed here, "
"remove this Attribute (the lack of wealth comes from the native economy; "
"Replicators would ignore it)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:71
msgid "Desolate"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:75
msgid ""
"This planet produces 4 less CP each Economic Phase during which there is "
"a Colony here, to a minimum of 0. Replicators do not produce a ship at "
"this planet during an Economic Phase unless the Colony is at Full and "
"they pay 3 CP, but a Replicator Colony at full strength may always be "
"used to join/split/reconfigure Replicator ships without cost (40.3.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:80
msgid "Sparta"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:84
msgid ""
"At the end of any Economic Phase during which there is a full-strength "
"Colony on this planet, that Colony additionally produces either one Space"
" Marine or one Heavy Infantry (if the Colony's owner does not have Ground"
" Combat 2 no unit is produced) If a Replicator Colony is placed on this "
"planet, remove this Attribute."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:85
msgid ""
"Text corrected per PAC Planets: 'does not have' — Card Manifest reads "
"'has Ground Combat 2 no unit is produced' (inverted condition, likely a "
"typo in the Card Manifest)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:89
msgid "Defensible"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:93
msgid ""
"All defending Ground Units (including Militia) on this planet get +1 "
"Defense Strength. There is no extra effect on colony bombardment rolls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:98
msgid "Dampening"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:102
msgid ""
"Because of a strong dampening field that interferes with FTL travel, all "
"ships must stop before and after entering this planet hex. All ships must"
" also stop after leaving this hex. Nothing can remove this movement "
"restriction, including MS Pipelines (13.2.1). However, an MS Pipeline can"
" still connect to the Colony and provide its standard increase to CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:103
msgid ""
"Text corrected per PAC Planets: added 'before and' to movement "
"restriction."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:107
msgid "Ambush"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:111
msgid ""
"All attacking ships (including LONGBOWMEN ships) in this hex fire as if "
"they are E-Class (this supersedes any effects from cards). Boarding Ships"
" still fire as F-Class. If a Replicator Colony is placed on this planet, "
"remove this Attribute."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:112
msgid ""
"Text corrected per PAC Planets: added '(including LONGBOWMEN ships)'. "
"Note: PAC Planets omits '(this supersedes any effects from cards)' — Card"
" Manifest includes it; text follows Card Manifest."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:116
msgid "Doomed"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:120
msgid ""
"When this planet is revealed, place a numeral marker with a 6 in the hex."
" Reduce the numerical marker by 1 each Economic Phase. When the numeral "
"marker should be reduced from 1 to 0, remove it instead. The planet "
"explodes and destroys all units in the hex; replace it with an Asteroid "
"counter (or terrain tile.) If this planet is removed for any other reason"
" (Titan attack, Replicator Colony depletion), remove this Attribute and "
"the numerical countdown marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:125
msgid "Builder"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:129
msgid ""
"When colonized, this planet provides 3 Hull Points of Shipyard build "
"capacity. These Hull Points are available as long as there is a Colony on"
" the planet, but they are not impacted by technology. If a Replicator "
"Colony is placed on this planet, remove this Attribute."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:130
msgid "Text replaced per PAC Planets: '3 Hull Points of Shipyard build capacity'."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:134
msgid "Spaceport"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:138
msgid ""
"This planet is a neutral spaceport and cannot be colonized or fired upon,"
" though it can be connected to a player's trade network as if it were a "
"Colony. It may not have Fighters or Ground Units on the planet. Combat "
"occurs normally in the hex, but the planet is always unaffected. A player"
" who has a unit in this hex at the start of the Economic Phase may build "
"one ship of Ship Size 1 in this hex for 2 CP more than that ship's usual "
"cost. A Raider using Cloak to avoid combat does not allow a player the "
"ability to build a ship here. A Replicator player may place one of their "
"Hulls at this planet instead of at the planet where it would have usually"
" been produced. That Hull will cost 1 CP additional."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:139
msgid "Text corrected per PAC Planets: Replicator rule reworded to match source."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:143
#: app/data/master_rulebook.py:4076
msgid "Research"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:147
msgid ""
"When colonized for the first time (only), this planet gives one level of "
"technology. Roll on the Space Wreck table. If a Replicator Colony is "
"placed on this planet, remove this Attribute and treat the Replicators as"
" if they consumed a Space Wreck, gaining 1 RP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:152
msgid "Minor Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:156
msgid ""
"Instead of drawing two Alien Technology Cards and choosing one (11.0), "
"the player draws three and chooses one. Replicators gain no additional "
"benefit; they draw one card and immediately discard it, gaining 10 CP as "
"normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:161
msgid "Major Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:165
msgid ""
"Instead of drawing two Alien Technology Cards and choosing one (11.0), "
"the player draws three and chooses two. Replicators draw two cards and "
"immediately discard both, gaining 20 CP (10 CP per card as normal)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:170
msgid "Cloaked"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:174
msgid ""
"All NPA ships in this planet hex have Cloaking 2 but will not cloak to "
"avoid combat. Replicators entering combat with these NPAs are treated as "
"encountering Cloaking, thereby unlocking Scanners."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:179
msgid "Ranged"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:183
msgid ""
"All NPA ships here fire as if they are one Weapon Class better. When this"
" planet is first colonized, the player gets 10 CP off the next level of "
"Tactics Technology they research (the counter is removed and kept as a "
"reminder). Replicators entering combat with these NPAs are treated as "
"encountering Tactics 2, potentially gaining an RP. If a Replicator Colony"
" is placed on this planet, remove this Attribute without further effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:184
#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:193
#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:202
#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:211
msgid ""
"PAC Planets reads 'take the planet counter as a reminder' — Card Manifest"
" reads 'the counter is removed and kept as a reminder'; text follows Card"
" Manifest."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:188
msgid "Accurate"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:192
msgid ""
"All NPA ships here have +1 to their Attack Strength. When this planet is "
"first colonized, the player gets 10 CP off the next Attack Technology "
"they research (the counter is removed and kept as a reminder). "
"Replicators entering combat with these NPAs are treated as encountering "
"Attack 1, potentially gaining an RP. If a Replicator Colony is placed on "
"this planet, remove this Attribute without further effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:197
msgid "Shielded"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:201
msgid ""
"All NPA ships here have +1 to their Defense Strength. When this planet is"
" first colonized, the player gets 10 CP off the next Defense Technology "
"they research (the counter is removed and kept as a reminder). "
"Replicators entering combat with these NPAs are treated as encountering "
"Defense 1, potentially gaining an RP. If a Replicator Colony is placed on"
" this planet, remove this Attribute without further effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:206
msgid "Giant"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:210
msgid ""
"All NPA ships here have +1 Hull Points except for determining if they are"
" equipped with Scanner or Point Defense technology. When this planet is "
"first colonized, the player gets 10 CP off the next Ship Size Technology "
"they research (the counter is removed and kept as a reminder). "
"Replicators entering combat with these NPAs are treated as encountering a"
" Cruiser, potentially gaining an RP. If a Replicator Colony is placed on "
"this planet, remove this Attribute without further effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:215
msgid "Military Geniuses"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:219
msgid ""
"All NPA ships here have +1 Attack and +1 Defense. When this planet is "
"colonized, the player draws two Crew Cards (12.0) and keeps one, which "
"can be used immediately or at the next Econ Phase. In addition, whenever "
"a Crew Card is used, it may be placed on a ship in this hex, if "
"colonized."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:220
msgid ""
"Text follows Card Manifest (full version). PAC Planets reads 'When this "
"planet is colonized, the player draws two Crew Cards (12.0) and keeps "
"one.' (shorter, without the usage rule). Previous version incorrectly "
"used 'has a Colony' instead of 'is colonized' (wrong per both sources)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:224
msgid "Jedun"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:228
msgid ""
"All NPA ships here have +1 Attack, +1 Defense, and +1 Tactics. When this "
"planet has a Colony, the owner may place one group (ships or Ground "
"Units) with up to 8 Hull Points under this counter; the group is studying"
" at the Jedun Temple. Only one group may be studying at the Jedun Temple "
"at a time and that group may not simultaneously upgrade their ships. If "
"it does not move for three consecutive turns, the group is marked with a "
"Jedun counter for the rest of the game. This group gets +1 Attack, +1 "
"Defense, +1 Tactics to its base stats. These bonuses are not considered "
"technological, but rather a consequence of the disciplined training the "
"crew received at the temple. It is possible for a group to have an "
"effective rating of Tactics 4 because of this. No units may be added to "
"this group unless they also have a Jedun counter and any Group split off "
"gains a Jedun counter. Jedun ships that are captured are no longer Jedun "
"(due to the change in crew). If a Replicator Colony is placed on this "
"planet or the planet is destroyed, remove this Attribute without further "
"effect; preexisting groups with Jedun counters retain their bonuses."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:229
msgid ""
"PAC Planets reads 'but from training at the Jedun temple' — Card Manifest"
" reads 'but rather a consequence of the disciplined training the crew "
"received at the temple'; text follows Card Manifest."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:233
msgid "Telepathic"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:237
msgid ""
"If a player has a Colony on this planet, their ships that start in the "
"hex and do not move may be placed under the Telepathic counter. At the "
"end of another player's movement phase (before ships are revealed in "
"combat), ships under the Telepathic counter may be placed in any battle "
"hex within range of what they could have moved to in their previous turn."
" They are considered part of the defending forces from the start of the "
"battle. They may also be placed in a hex adjacent to the Colony with no "
"enemy combat units present. They may do this even if their hex has an "
"attacking fleet in it. This represents the people of the planet warning "
"them of where enemy units are going to move and thereby being able to "
"intercept or avoid them. If a Replicator Colony is placed on this planet,"
" remove this Attribute."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:242
msgid "Scanning"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:246
msgid ""
"There is a massive scanning array built into this planet which is far "
"beyond the technology of the players. If a player has a Colony on this "
"planet, all enemy ships within 2 hexes of the planet are flipped to their"
" revealed side (immediately when the colony is placed and immediately "
"when ships enter later). If a Replicator Colony is on the planet, they "
"receive the same benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:251
msgid "Time Dilation"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/deep_space_planet_attributes.py:255
msgid ""
"Time moves twice as fast on this planet. During the Economic Phase, a "
"Colony on this planet grows twice and produces twice. A Colony with a 1 "
"marker, produce 1 CP, grow to a 3 marker, produce 3 CP, and then grow to "
"a 5 marker in one Economic Phase. Twice as many Shipyards or Bases can be"
" produced in one Economic Phase as is normally allowed and each existing "
"Shipyard can produce twice as many ships. The first (or only) Shipyard "
"built on this planet during any one Economic Phase may produce a normal "
"number of ships in that Economic Phase. After combat, the planet may be "
"bombarded by each ship twice. Replicator Colonies are not affected as "
"described above. Replicator Colonies that begin an Economic Phase at full"
" growth may build a single Hull Size 2 ship directly instead of creating "
"two Hull Size 1 ships."
msgstr ""

