#: app/data/scenarios.py:1868
msgid ""
"11.0 Alien Empire Coop (2-Player) - Victory Point Rules\n"
"\n"
"11.1 Setup\n"
"Same as solitaire section 6.0 except as noted.\n"
"\n"
"11.1.1 Extermination Fleet Targeting: If launched during an odd numbered "
"Economic Phase, target is the Galactic Capitol. Otherwise, target nearest"
" player Homeworld.\n"
"\n"
"11.2 AP Difficulty - 2-Player COOP:\n"
"Easy: 2 APs, 5 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 150, Max Defense 50\n"
"Normal: 2 APs, 10 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 150, Max Defense 50\n"
"Hard: 2 APs, 15 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 150, Max Defense 50\n"
"\n"
"11.3 Victory Conditions: AP wins if 10 VP collected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenarios.py:1884
msgid "Alien Empire Coop (3-Player) — Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenarios.py:1892
msgid "3-player cooperative version of the Alien Empire VP scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenarios.py:1893
msgid ""
"12.0 Alien Empire Coop (3-Player) - Victory Point Rules\n"
"\n"
"12.1 Setup\n"
"Same as solitaire section 6.0 except as noted.\n"
"\n"
"12.1.1 Starting Home Systems: Most experienced player uses Player 1 area."
"\n"
"\n"
"12.1.2 Deep Space Markers: Placed on every white hex not otherwise "
"marked.\n"
"\n"
"12.1.3 Aliens: \"AP\" marks Homeworlds. Two APs represented by one color "
"but treated as separate empires. Use spare counters as needed.\n"
"\n"
"12.1.4 Extermination Fleet Targeting: Odd Economic Phase targets GC. "
"Otherwise targets Homeworld of player with least CP income.\n"
"\n"
"12.1.5 Expansion/Raider Fleets: Must spend at least one Economic Phase in"
" Deep Space before entering a player's Home System.\n"
"\n"
"12.2 AP Difficulty - 3-Player COOP:\n"
"Easy: 2 APs, 10 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 200, Max Defense 50\n"
"Normal: 2 APs, 10 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 200, Max Defense 50\n"
"Hard: 2 APs, 20 CP/Econ, Starting Bank 200, Max Defense 50\n"
"\n"
"12.3 Victory Conditions: AP wins if 10 VP collected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenarios.py:1917
msgid "AP Bot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenarios.py:1923
msgid ""
"New mode replacing the automated Alien Player with a more sophisticated "
"bot that emulates a human player. Can substitute in almost any scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/scenarios.py:1924
msgid ""
"13.0 AP Bot\n"
"\n"
"13.1 Purpose\n"
"New mode making the AP act more like a player substitute or \"bot\". Can "
"be used in almost any previously published scenario. Treat this set of "
"rules as completely different from the solo/coop scenarios above. The "
"flowcharts at the end of this scenario book do NOT apply to this "
"iteration of the AP Bot.\n"
"\n"
"13.2 Definitions\n"
"• 1d100: Two d10 generating 1-100.\n"
"• AP/AP bot: Used interchangeably.\n"
"• EV: Exploration Vessel. FOB: Forward Operating Base. HS: Home System.\n"
"• Known AP Fleet: Technology tracked on spare Production Sheet. Can "
"become Unknown again.\n"
"• Map Size: Number of DS hexes on shortest route between AP and nearest "
"Player HS at game start.\n"
"• Player: Human player. SCT: Special Counter Tech.\n"
"• Unknown AP Fleet: Face down fleet with unknown units/technology.\n"
"\n"
"13.3 Prime Directive\n"
"Where the rules are silent or conflict, use common sense and play your "
"opponent intelligently. This rule supersedes all other rulings. Do not "
"alter the AP's Strategy after employing the Prime Directive.\n"
"\n"
"13.4 Scenarios\n"
"The revised AP can substitute for a human player in most scenarios (e.g. "
"CSB 2.2 2-Player Standard).\n"
"\n"
"13.4.1 Expansion Goals Table:\n"
"Map Size <2: 0 DS Colonies, 1 EV, 0 Max Terraform, Move Roll 2\n"
"Map Size 2: 0 DS Colonies, 1 EV, 0 Max Terraform, Move Roll 3\n"
"Map Size 4: 1 DS Colony, 2 EVs, 1 Max Terraform, Move Roll 5\n"
"Map Size 6: 2 DS Colonies, 3 EVs, 2 Max Terraform, Move Roll 7\n"
"Map Size 8: 2 DS Colonies, 3 EVs, 2 Max Terraform, Move Roll 9\n"
"Map Size >8: 3 DS Colonies, 4 EVs, 2 Max Terraform, Move Roll 9\n"
"\n"
"13.5 First Player: Decided randomly (MRB 3.0). AP always resolves Econ "
"Phase after players.\n"
"\n"
"13.6 New Hidden Galactic Capitol Rules: See separate entry.\n"
"\n"
"13.7 Lost in Space Resolution: See 1.1.9.\n"
"\n"
"13.8 Regional Map Resolution: For AP or players, flip and resolve all "
"eligible adjacent hexes as if flipped by Exploration technology.\n"
"\n"
"13.9 Player Alliance Rules: Players need not use alliance rules. AP "
"treats all Players as if allied.\n"
"\n"
"13.10 AP Alliances: APs have UNEASY ALLIANCE but don't share information."
" Operate completely separately.\n"
"\n"
"13.11 Victory Points: AP scenarios no longer use VPs. Colony Point rule "
"(CSB 1.1.7) may be used instead.\n"
"\n"
"13.12 Galactic Capitol: If used, AP may randomly target GC as another HW "
"for Extermination. If GC captured/eliminated, AP wins.\n"
"\n"
"13.13 Number of Alien Players: Should generally equal number of human "
"players. For extra challenge, add one AP and decrease Difficulty by one "
"step."
msgstr ""

